WEBVTT

00:00:40.674 --> 00:00:43.735
<i>Sometimes all it
takes is a spark.</i>

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:46.536
<i>Something very small.</i>

00:00:46.647 --> 00:00:49.173
<i>But the spark becomes a flame.</i>

00:00:49.283 --> 00:00:51.218
<i>And if that flame spreads,</i>

00:00:51.318 --> 00:00:53.310
<i>the power can be so overwhelming</i>

00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:55.082
<i>it transforms
everything around it.</i>

00:00:56.523 --> 00:00:58.134
<i>We begin with breaking news from</i>

00:00:58.158 --> 00:00:59.802
<i>- Hope Springs, Arkansas...
- People are up</i>

00:00:59.826 --> 00:01:01.738
<i>in arms, speaking out
against what they believe...</i>

00:01:01.762 --> 00:01:03.806
<i>only religious leader
who refused to abide...</i>

00:01:03.830 --> 00:01:05.822
<i>David Hill, you're under arrest.</i>

00:01:06.133 --> 00:01:07.431
<i>Contempt of court.</i>

00:01:07.534 --> 00:01:09.245
<i>You failed to produce your
sermons upon court order.</i>

00:01:09.269 --> 00:01:10.794
<i>Please put your hands
behind your back.</i>

00:01:11.104 --> 00:01:13.573
<i>Who feel the state is
overstepping its bounds.</i>

00:01:17.411 --> 00:01:19.403
<i>A subpoena of
sermons is needless</i>

00:01:19.513 --> 00:01:21.291
<i>- and unprecedented.
- This is a witch hunt</i>

00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:22.408
<i>to silence religion...</i>

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:34.423
<i>We're seeing more</i>

00:01:34.528 --> 00:01:36.429
<i>and more protests
around the city</i>

00:01:36.530 --> 00:01:38.123
since local pastor, David Hill,

00:01:38.231 --> 00:01:39.859
was arrested for
contempt of court.

00:01:40.167 --> 00:01:41.863
Hill refused to abide
by a controversial

00:01:42.169 --> 00:01:44.866
<i>government mandate
to turn over transcripts</i>

00:01:45.172 --> 00:01:46.504
<i>of his sermons
to city officials.</i>

00:01:46.607 --> 00:01:48.576
<i>And right now a
contentious and heated</i>

00:01:48.675 --> 00:01:50.576
<i>free-speech debate is
threatening to boil over</i>

00:01:50.677 --> 00:01:54.444
<i>while the pastor sits in
jail waiting for a ruling.</i>

00:02:04.157 --> 00:02:05.853
Let's go.

00:02:19.473 --> 00:02:21.135
Appreciate it.

00:02:21.241 --> 00:02:23.176
- Hey.
- Jude.

00:02:27.748 --> 00:02:29.478
You want to get some waffles?

00:02:29.583 --> 00:02:32.417
Of course I want
to get some waffles.

00:02:32.519 --> 00:02:35.717
Free Reverend Dave!
Free Reverend Dave!

00:02:35.822 --> 00:02:38.155
Free Reverend Dave!

00:02:38.258 --> 00:02:39.636
<i>Reverend, what
do you have to say</i>

00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:41.151
<i>about being released today?</i>

00:02:41.261 --> 00:02:43.287
I am grateful to the
court that they recognize

00:02:43.397 --> 00:02:45.263
that this mandate
was unconstitutional.

00:02:45.365 --> 00:02:47.391
I think this is more of
a human rights issue.

00:02:47.501 --> 00:02:48.901
It's about our
right to seek truth

00:02:49.202 --> 00:02:51.171
and to share that
truth with others.

00:02:51.271 --> 00:02:52.582
<i>But considering your church</i>

00:02:52.606 --> 00:02:54.165
<i>is associated with
a public university,</i>

00:02:54.274 --> 00:02:56.573
how do you define
"truth" exactly?

00:02:56.677 --> 00:02:59.476
Truth is a person.

00:02:59.579 --> 00:03:01.775
The person of Jesus Christ.

00:03:01.882 --> 00:03:03.407
It's the one truth

00:03:03.517 --> 00:03:05.349
- above all others.
- What do you have to say

00:03:05.452 --> 00:03:07.478
to the people here
who are calling...

00:03:07.587 --> 00:03:10.887
<i>Jesus Christ is the
one truth? Really?</i>

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:12.635
This guy just can't
help himself, can he?

00:03:12.659 --> 00:03:15.424
This guy is a pastor who
was jailed for his beliefs.

00:03:15.529 --> 00:03:18.192
<i>What if it was a Jewish rabbi
that said there was one truth?</i>

00:03:18.298 --> 00:03:20.267
<i>- Or a Muslim imam?
- They have that right.</i>

00:03:20.367 --> 00:03:22.359
<i>- Freedom of worship.
- In places of worship.</i>

00:03:22.469 --> 00:03:24.404
But Hadleigh is
a state university.

00:03:24.504 --> 00:03:25.915
<i>See, and that's
the question, y'all.</i>

00:03:25.939 --> 00:03:27.567
What's a church doing
on a state campus

00:03:27.674 --> 00:03:29.700
- in the first place?
- We're seeing more and more

00:03:29.810 --> 00:03:31.854
<i>- protests around the city.
- Students are actually calling</i>

00:03:31.878 --> 00:03:33.312
for the removal of Saint James

00:03:33.413 --> 00:03:34.693
<i>from Hadleigh campus altogether.</i>

00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:36.444
As the battle rages
on in Hope Springs...

00:03:36.550 --> 00:03:37.894
<i>A historic landmark that has</i>

00:03:37.918 --> 00:03:39.784
<i>served this community
for over a century.</i>

00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:41.821
<i>And now they want
the church gone.</i>

00:03:41.922 --> 00:03:44.619
<i>This is what our
country has come to.</i>

00:04:01.842 --> 00:04:04.004
You gonna ask her out or what?

00:04:04.311 --> 00:04:05.574
Excuse me?

00:04:05.679 --> 00:04:08.615
We drive all the way
out here every week,

00:04:08.715 --> 00:04:10.013
drop off all this food.

00:04:10.317 --> 00:04:12.252
Why don't you
finally ask the girl out?

00:04:12.352 --> 00:04:13.820
She feeds homeless people, Jude.

00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:15.445
That's why we donate the food.

00:04:15.555 --> 00:04:17.285
Yes, but she
obviously likes you.

00:04:17.390 --> 00:04:19.586
No way.

00:04:19.693 --> 00:04:22.356
What's a six-letter
word for "clueless"?

00:04:22.462 --> 00:04:23.896
Fine.

00:04:23.997 --> 00:04:26.023
You're still working
on that thing?

00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.529
I'm much faster
when it's in Swahili.

00:04:28.635 --> 00:04:31.298
Fair enough.

00:04:32.906 --> 00:04:34.283
<i>This tab's already been paid.</i>

00:04:34.307 --> 00:04:36.367
You guys enjoy.

00:04:37.844 --> 00:04:39.745
- Hey, convict.
- Hey.

00:04:39.846 --> 00:04:41.838
<i>Just can't stay out of the news</i>

00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:43.678
these days, can you?

00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:46.549
Yeah, I've never had so
many people care what I think.

00:04:46.653 --> 00:04:48.884
Well, I'm on your
side. You know that.

00:04:48.989 --> 00:04:50.514
Busy today, huh?

00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:51.819
Busy's good.

00:04:51.925 --> 00:04:53.325
The more people
we feed, the better.

00:04:53.426 --> 00:04:55.554
Hey, thank your
congregation for all this.

00:04:55.662 --> 00:04:56.994
Couldn't do it without y'all.

00:04:57.297 --> 00:05:00.062
- I'll see you next Saturday.
- Hold up.

00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:05.601
From last night.

00:05:05.705 --> 00:05:07.731
Pork chops turned out great.

00:05:07.841 --> 00:05:09.469
Thanks.

00:05:22.656 --> 00:05:23.885
Told you.

00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:25.856
Who asked you?

00:05:43.877 --> 00:05:45.641
<i>Wonder what my
father would think.</i>

00:05:45.745 --> 00:05:48.738
When he was a pastor,
he'd leave these doors open

00:05:48.849 --> 00:05:50.841
day and night... didn't matter.

00:05:50.951 --> 00:05:53.614
Now we hire armed
security guards

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:55.450
to protect us from
the same people

00:05:55.555 --> 00:05:57.023
we're supposed
to be ministering to.

00:05:57.123 --> 00:05:59.820
It's just fear, David,
and it can be overcome.

00:05:59.926 --> 00:06:01.554
You know this.

00:06:01.661 --> 00:06:03.027
Do you ever complain?

00:06:03.129 --> 00:06:04.597
You know where I come from.

00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:06.667
I've seen my share of struggles.

00:06:06.766 --> 00:06:09.736
But one thing has never changed.

00:06:09.836 --> 00:06:12.738
God is good all the time.

00:06:12.839 --> 00:06:15.900
All the time, God is good.

00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:19.641
<i>I appreciate you all</i>

00:06:19.746 --> 00:06:21.977
<i>braving the angry mobs
and picketers again.</i>

00:06:22.082 --> 00:06:23.812
But even with all the noise

00:06:23.917 --> 00:06:26.443
going on out there, I
just want to assure you

00:06:26.553 --> 00:06:29.990
that Saint James has been
around for over 150 years,

00:06:30.090 --> 00:06:32.753
and despite what those
picket signs say out there,

00:06:32.859 --> 00:06:35.556
- we're not going anywhere.
- Amen.

00:06:35.662 --> 00:06:38.689
Now, looking forward, I
have some very good news.

00:06:38.798 --> 00:06:41.165
Jude, you want to come up?

00:06:44.504 --> 00:06:49.465
I couldn't be happier to share
that our very own Jude Mbaye

00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:51.135
has accepted a
permanent position

00:06:51.444 --> 00:06:54.744
with us here at Saint
James as my co-pastor.

00:06:54.848 --> 00:06:56.817
Amen. Welcome, brother.

00:06:56.917 --> 00:06:58.647
Thank you.

00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:02.552
You know, I realized
tonight that, uh,

00:07:02.656 --> 00:07:04.522
it's been a long
time since I've felt

00:07:04.624 --> 00:07:06.525
like I had a real
brother in my life.

00:07:08.128 --> 00:07:10.996
David, are you
sharing your feelings?

00:07:11.097 --> 00:07:13.032
Okay, let's not make
a big deal out of it.

00:07:13.133 --> 00:07:16.126
I'm just saying that
I'm grateful for you.

00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.462
I'm excited.

00:07:18.571 --> 00:07:19.834
I feel the same.

00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:21.704
Now can we get some waffles?

00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:27.145
- What was that?
- I don't know.

00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:33.818
- Hey! Hey! Get back here!
- David!

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:35.650
David, no!

00:07:46.066 --> 00:07:47.625
You call the police.

00:07:47.734 --> 00:07:50.169
- I'll shut off the alarm.
- Yeah.

00:07:52.706 --> 00:07:54.231
<i>Yeah, this is, uh,
Reverend David Hill.</i>

00:07:54.541 --> 00:07:56.942
I'm a... I'm a pastor
at Saint James.

00:08:09.222 --> 00:08:11.123
<i>Well, no, it's not an emergency.</i>

00:08:11.224 --> 00:08:13.750
It's just a, uh... it
was a broken window

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:14.987
<i>to the basement.</i>

00:08:38.952 --> 00:08:40.545
Jude?

00:08:41.821 --> 00:08:43.187
Jude?

00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:49.827
Jude?

00:08:54.801 --> 00:08:57.168
Jude?

00:08:58.238 --> 00:08:59.238
Oh, no.

00:08:59.272 --> 00:09:00.865
David...

00:09:00.974 --> 00:09:02.670
You're gonna be okay.

00:09:02.776 --> 00:09:05.109
All right? Stay with me.

00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:06.736
Okay.

00:09:10.083 --> 00:09:11.949
Come on, pal.

00:09:27.967 --> 00:09:30.266
Jude, I'm gonna
get you out of here.

00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:31.936
- Okay. Okay.
- Okay?

00:09:32.038 --> 00:09:33.973
Stay with me.

00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.878
Please, God, help me.

00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:07.297
David...

00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:08.973
Don't talk, brother. Don't talk.

00:10:09.075 --> 00:10:10.373
Just stay with me.

00:10:10.677 --> 00:10:12.145
Help is coming.

00:10:12.245 --> 00:10:14.111
Hold on, Jude. It's okay.

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:18.348
What?

00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:24.200
What are you saying?

00:10:24.224 --> 00:10:25.749
What does that mean?

00:10:25.859 --> 00:10:28.124
Jude?

00:10:28.228 --> 00:10:30.322
Jude.

00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:32.121
Jude.

00:10:33.700 --> 00:10:35.100
Please, God, no.

00:10:35.201 --> 00:10:36.396
Jude. Help!

00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:38.995
Stay with me, brother.

00:10:39.105 --> 00:10:41.973
Jude...

00:10:47.680 --> 00:10:49.273
No.

00:11:29.956 --> 00:11:32.221
<i>I'm so tired of all the noise.</i>

00:11:33.927 --> 00:11:36.260
<i>Everyone yelling.</i>

00:11:36.362 --> 00:11:37.853
<i>On the news.</i>

00:11:37.964 --> 00:11:39.296
<i>In the classroom.</i>

00:11:40.767 --> 00:11:42.429
<i>Even in church.</i>

00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:46.730
<i>I can barely hear You anymore.</i>

00:11:53.246 --> 00:11:55.442
<i>Are You even there?</i>

00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:00.880
<i>I hope You are.</i>

00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:06.359
<i>'Cause I feel so lost, God.</i>

00:12:07.860 --> 00:12:09.351
I'm starting to feel pretty dumb

00:12:09.462 --> 00:12:12.261
talking to myself when
You don't talk back, so...

00:12:14.334 --> 00:12:17.862
Wherever You are...

00:12:17.971 --> 00:12:20.031
I'm still here.

00:12:21.808 --> 00:12:23.276
Hey.

00:12:23.376 --> 00:12:25.038
Hi.

00:12:25.144 --> 00:12:27.443
I stopped at Stella's,
got you the good stuff.

00:12:27.747 --> 00:12:29.225
- You're my hero. Thank you.
- I know.

00:12:29.249 --> 00:12:30.376
You're welcome.

00:12:30.483 --> 00:12:32.748
- How's your day?
- Good.

00:12:32.852 --> 00:12:36.983
Wow, this looks, uh, fun.

00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:41.257
You can get it if you want.

00:12:42.428 --> 00:12:43.794
It's Sunday.

00:12:43.896 --> 00:12:44.896
Oh, that's right.

00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.900
You're... "in church."

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:48.229
Don't be a jerk.

00:12:48.334 --> 00:12:49.495
Why don't you just tell 'em?

00:12:49.802 --> 00:12:51.293
Adam, my parents
would be devastated

00:12:51.404 --> 00:12:53.305
if they found out I
was even questioning.

00:12:53.406 --> 00:12:54.999
Okay, you have no idea.

00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:56.337
Yeah, I do.

00:12:56.442 --> 00:12:58.877
I did my time as
a kid, remember?

00:12:58.978 --> 00:13:01.174
I just got out
sooner than you did.

00:13:01.281 --> 00:13:03.182
Okay, can we
not talk about this?

00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:06.480
Sure.

00:13:09.555 --> 00:13:11.183
I get it.

00:13:12.358 --> 00:13:14.350
What you're going through.

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:16.486
I really do.

00:13:19.098 --> 00:13:20.327
Okay, go to your study group.

00:13:20.433 --> 00:13:21.799
I have work to do.

00:13:21.901 --> 00:13:24.268
- Are you kicking me out?
- Mm-hmm.

00:13:24.370 --> 00:13:26.032
Fine.

00:13:26.139 --> 00:13:27.903
- See you later.
- Okay. Bye.

00:13:28.007 --> 00:13:29.498
Thanks for the snack.

00:13:42.955 --> 00:13:44.287
<i>Okay, wait, wait.</i>

00:13:44.390 --> 00:13:46.110
<i>So, let me get this straight.</i>

00:13:46.192 --> 00:13:48.252
<i>So, you're saying</i>

00:13:48.361 --> 00:13:50.592
that because the Kit Kat
logo doesn't have a hyphen,

00:13:50.897 --> 00:13:52.923
it proves there are
multiple realities?

00:13:53.032 --> 00:13:54.392
Okay, look, you're
oversimplifying,

00:13:54.434 --> 00:13:56.245
- but yes, exactly.
- How am I oversimplifying?

00:13:56.269 --> 00:13:57.413
That's exactly what you said.

00:13:57.437 --> 00:13:58.847
Yeah, but it's not
just Kit Kat, though.

00:13:58.871 --> 00:13:59.871
It's a lot of things.

00:13:59.906 --> 00:14:00.983
- Like what?
- Like... like Curious George

00:14:01.007 --> 00:14:02.839
used to have a tail,
but now he doesn't.

00:14:02.942 --> 00:14:04.535
- What?
- "Used to"?

00:14:04.844 --> 00:14:06.972
- Yeah. Look it up.
- No, it didn't change.

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:09.425
- People just remember it wrong.
- Okay, but maybe it did change.

00:14:09.449 --> 00:14:11.193
- Maybe it did change.
- Wait, wait, whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:14:11.217 --> 00:14:13.209
Curious George
does not have a tail?

00:14:13.319 --> 00:14:15.413
- No.
- On it.

00:14:15.521 --> 00:14:17.422
My whole life's a lie.

00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:19.568
- This is freaking me out.
- You haven't heard about this?

00:14:19.592 --> 00:14:22.084
- No.
- No, it's called the Mandela Effect.

00:14:22.195 --> 00:14:24.221
Millions of people thought
that Nelson Mandela

00:14:24.330 --> 00:14:25.923
died in prison in the '80s,

00:14:26.032 --> 00:14:27.443
- but he didn't.
- The theory is our reality

00:14:27.467 --> 00:14:29.060
collided with a
parallel reality.

00:14:29.168 --> 00:14:31.296
Right, right, right... Where
Kit Kat has no hyphen

00:14:31.404 --> 00:14:33.134
and Curious George has no tail.

00:14:33.239 --> 00:14:34.366
Oh, okay.

00:14:34.474 --> 00:14:36.033
Look, it's science, yo, okay?

00:14:36.142 --> 00:14:38.354
- Quantum physics... look it up.
- "Quantum physics."

00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.422
Do you guys seriously not
hear how ridiculous you sound?

00:14:40.446 --> 00:14:41.971
Okay, but God had
Himself a human son

00:14:42.081 --> 00:14:43.459
who could walk on
water and multiply fish,

00:14:43.483 --> 00:14:44.974
and that's not ridiculous?

00:14:45.084 --> 00:14:48.077
So, yeah, given the choice,
I'm taking the Kit Kat theory.

00:14:48.187 --> 00:14:49.951
And if we get lucky,
maybe we'll collide

00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:52.548
with a reality where our school
isn't poisoned by Reverend Dave

00:14:52.658 --> 00:14:55.025
- and his one truth.
- Preach it.

00:14:55.128 --> 00:14:57.256
You just don't get it
'cause you're one of 'em, K.

00:14:57.363 --> 00:14:58.956
Not really.

00:14:59.065 --> 00:15:01.091
I mean, not anymore.

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:02.327
Excuse me?

00:15:03.603 --> 00:15:05.333
- What?
- Okay, if-if you're not

00:15:05.438 --> 00:15:07.669
one of them, then what are you?

00:15:07.974 --> 00:15:09.909
What am I?

00:15:10.009 --> 00:15:11.033
I'm annoyed.

00:15:11.144 --> 00:15:12.976
By you, because you're annoying.

00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:14.570
I have to go.

00:15:17.683 --> 00:15:19.549
- Sorry, bro. I...
- Thanks, Teo.

00:15:19.652 --> 00:15:21.314
It was a... conversation.

00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:23.151
It's okay.

00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:26.188
Keaton, wait up.

00:15:26.292 --> 00:15:27.652
Look, I didn't
mean anything by it.

00:15:27.927 --> 00:15:28.927
I know. It's fine.

00:15:28.961 --> 00:15:30.190
I have a chem test tomorrow.

00:15:30.296 --> 00:15:32.424
- I have to study.
- We were just joking.

00:15:32.532 --> 00:15:35.024
Keaton.

00:15:35.134 --> 00:15:37.296
I don't care what you
believe and don't believe,

00:15:37.403 --> 00:15:38.647
and I don't have a
problem with God.

00:15:38.671 --> 00:15:40.230
Yeah, but you do, Adam.

00:15:40.339 --> 00:15:41.659
Okay? You say
it's just the church

00:15:41.707 --> 00:15:43.471
or religion or whatever, but...

00:15:45.645 --> 00:15:48.945
You know, I am so tired of
having this same conversation

00:15:49.048 --> 00:15:51.415
- over and over again with you.
- Yeah. Me, too.

00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.387
I-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

00:15:58.991 --> 00:16:00.289
Okay?

00:16:01.627 --> 00:16:03.095
I know.

00:16:03.196 --> 00:16:04.630
Okay.

00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.302
I think I...

00:16:14.307 --> 00:16:16.674
Think I just need
some time right now.

00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:21.204
On my own.

00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:24.678
What does that mean?

00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:27.283
Just to figure things out.

00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:31.590
Are you serious?

00:16:31.691 --> 00:16:33.216
No, come on.

00:16:33.326 --> 00:16:34.658
Don't...

00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:36.626
Don't do that.

00:16:36.729 --> 00:16:38.721
Keaton, please,
what are you doing?

00:16:39.031 --> 00:16:40.693
Don't.

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:42.559
I love you.

00:16:44.237 --> 00:16:46.035
I know.

00:16:46.138 --> 00:16:48.664
I love you. Don't do this.

00:16:49.775 --> 00:16:51.403
I'm sorry.

00:16:59.519 --> 00:17:02.182
All the time, God is good.

00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:16.230
♪ You're alive in us ♪

00:17:16.335 --> 00:17:19.430
♪ And we'll never be the same ♪

00:17:19.539 --> 00:17:21.508
♪ No ♪

00:17:21.607 --> 00:17:26.102
♪ We'll never be
the same, yeah ♪

00:17:26.212 --> 00:17:29.307
♪ We'll never be the same. ♪

00:17:34.787 --> 00:17:36.722
Dear God: Thank
You for Harbor House.

00:17:36.822 --> 00:17:38.381
Lord, we're broken people.

00:17:38.491 --> 00:17:39.668
Please just bring
healing and restoration

00:17:39.692 --> 00:17:41.251
to our school right now,

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:42.760
um, in this really
difficult time.

00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.122
We love You and answer
to Your beautiful name.

00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:47.291
- Amen. Thanks, guys.
- Amen.

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:49.062
Have a good one.

00:17:56.208 --> 00:17:57.437
Hey.

00:17:57.543 --> 00:17:59.842
I know, I know. I've been M.I.A.

00:18:00.146 --> 00:18:01.523
It's just been a
really crazy semester.

00:18:01.547 --> 00:18:03.140
Yeah, no, I-I totally get it.

00:18:03.249 --> 00:18:04.793
Well, look, you're...
you're more than welcome

00:18:04.817 --> 00:18:06.479
to come down to
the city and work

00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:08.214
on our habitat
project, if you want.

00:18:08.321 --> 00:18:11.189
Cool. Yeah, I'll...
I'll definitely try.

00:18:13.125 --> 00:18:15.594
Did you know that there's
no hyphen in "Kit Kat"?

00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:19.258
You mean like Kit
Kat, the candy bar?

00:18:20.666 --> 00:18:22.601
Yeah. You know what? Sorry.

00:18:22.702 --> 00:18:24.022
Forget it. I'm
being really weird.

00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.332
Hey.

00:18:25.438 --> 00:18:27.839
If you need to talk
about anything or...

00:18:28.140 --> 00:18:30.541
whatever, I'm-I'm always here.

00:18:30.643 --> 00:18:32.771
Thanks, but I'm fine, really.

00:18:32.878 --> 00:18:34.506
See ya.

00:19:16.188 --> 00:19:17.766
See, this here is
why you should never

00:19:17.790 --> 00:19:19.156
talk religion or politics, yo.

00:19:19.258 --> 00:19:21.386
Dude, that's all you talk about.

00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:24.157
Will you have Keaton text
me when you get back?

00:19:24.263 --> 00:19:25.561
Oh, uh-uh.

00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:26.826
Leave me out of this.

00:19:26.932 --> 00:19:28.457
This one is on you, Adam.

00:19:28.567 --> 00:19:30.798
If she wants to text
you, she will text you.

00:19:34.273 --> 00:19:36.833
All right, look, you
need to sleep it off, man.

00:19:36.942 --> 00:19:38.274
All right?

00:19:38.377 --> 00:19:39.640
- I'm fine.
- You good?

00:19:39.745 --> 00:19:40.940
Yeah.

00:19:41.247 --> 00:19:42.772
All right, man,
we're going this way.

00:19:42.882 --> 00:19:44.316
Later.

00:19:49.955 --> 00:19:52.447
Yeah, right.

00:20:42.341 --> 00:20:44.367
Hey!

00:20:44.477 --> 00:20:46.503
- Hey! Get back here!
- David!

00:20:46.612 --> 00:20:48.410
David, no!

00:20:56.522 --> 00:20:57.854
<i>The city was in shock</i>

00:20:57.957 --> 00:20:59.585
<i>late last night
when a tragic fire</i>

00:20:59.692 --> 00:21:01.354
<i>broke out at Saint James.</i>

00:21:01.460 --> 00:21:02.894
<i>That is the controversial church</i>

00:21:02.995 --> 00:21:05.692
on the campus of our very
own Hadleigh University.

00:21:05.798 --> 00:21:07.562
Both police and fire departments

00:21:07.666 --> 00:21:10.329
have not ruled out arson
in the fire that has claimed

00:21:10.436 --> 00:21:12.428
the life of a visiting
pastor from Ghana,

00:21:12.538 --> 00:21:13.904
Jude Mbaye.

00:21:14.006 --> 00:21:16.635
<i>Police and the FBI are
now treating the case</i>

00:21:16.742 --> 00:21:18.904
<i>as a hate-crime homicide.</i>

00:21:19.011 --> 00:21:21.537
Crowds have already started
to gather outside the church

00:21:21.647 --> 00:21:23.343
to pay their respects.

00:21:23.449 --> 00:21:24.815
This is why a church

00:21:24.917 --> 00:21:26.715
does not belong
on a state campus.

00:21:26.819 --> 00:21:28.363
You're favoring one
religion over another,

00:21:28.387 --> 00:21:29.548
of course people are angry.

00:21:29.655 --> 00:21:32.523
It just invites
violence like this.

00:21:32.625 --> 00:21:35.618
What else is it gonna
take for people to wake up?

00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:40.110
<i>The church has brought
nothing but controversy</i>

00:21:40.332 --> 00:21:42.426
to the school for
years. It's time.

00:21:42.535 --> 00:21:44.504
Our enrollment is down 18%.

00:21:44.603 --> 00:21:47.573
We stand to lose $15
million this year alone.

00:21:47.673 --> 00:21:49.005
I am well aware of that,

00:21:49.308 --> 00:21:51.800
but we can't pin all
of this on Saint James.

00:21:51.911 --> 00:21:53.812
Well, this university
is in the midst

00:21:53.913 --> 00:21:56.974
of an identity crisis, Tom,
because of Saint James.

00:21:57.082 --> 00:21:58.573
We're moving backwards.

00:21:58.684 --> 00:21:59.811
This is wrong.

00:21:59.919 --> 00:22:02.411
The church is a
historic landmark.

00:22:02.521 --> 00:22:04.854
It was here before
the university.

00:22:04.957 --> 00:22:06.858
Dave...

00:22:06.959 --> 00:22:09.394
is a good man.

00:22:09.495 --> 00:22:12.397
What about Jude,
the one who died?

00:22:12.498 --> 00:22:14.558
I'm sure he was a good man, too.

00:22:14.667 --> 00:22:17.102
Barbara, with all due respect,

00:22:17.403 --> 00:22:19.872
if we kick the church
off campus now

00:22:19.972 --> 00:22:21.565
after what just happened,

00:22:21.674 --> 00:22:23.040
how do you think
that's gonna look?

00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:25.743
We're gonna look bad
no matter what we do.

00:22:25.845 --> 00:22:29.543
But in the long run, this is
what's best for the students.

00:22:30.616 --> 00:22:32.847
Okay.

00:22:32.952 --> 00:22:35.114
Tom... I think you should be

00:22:35.421 --> 00:22:36.855
the one to talk to
Reverend Dave.

00:22:38.991 --> 00:22:41.017
Dave is my friend.

00:22:41.126 --> 00:22:43.561
Exactly.

00:23:05.451 --> 00:23:09.479
♪ Glory, glory ♪

00:23:11.790 --> 00:23:14.817
♪ Hallelujah ♪

00:23:17.730 --> 00:23:20.700
♪ Since I've laid my ♪

00:23:22.935 --> 00:23:26.133
♪ My burdens down... ♪

00:23:27.907 --> 00:23:31.776
My first message, my
friends from Saint James:

00:23:31.877 --> 00:23:33.903
We love you.

00:23:34.013 --> 00:23:36.915
We are grieving
right alongside you.

00:23:37.016 --> 00:23:40.180
Consider us your home
for as long as you need.

00:23:40.486 --> 00:23:45.823
<i>My second message
in this difficult hour:</i>

00:23:45.925 --> 00:23:46.984
<i>the same one</i>

00:23:47.092 --> 00:23:49.084
that Peter, John and James spoke

00:23:49.194 --> 00:23:52.892
on that one dark night
when all their hopes died

00:23:52.998 --> 00:23:55.024
on that blood-stained Cross.

00:23:55.134 --> 00:23:58.662
Weeping may last
through the night,

00:23:58.771 --> 00:24:02.139
but joy cometh in the morning.

00:24:02.441 --> 00:24:04.774
And the morning always comes.

00:24:04.877 --> 00:24:09.781
♪ Yes, I'm going home to ♪

00:24:09.882 --> 00:24:16.880
♪ To live with Jesus ♪

00:24:16.989 --> 00:24:20.619
♪ Since I've laid ♪

00:24:20.726 --> 00:24:24.720
♪ My burdens down. ♪

00:24:29.201 --> 00:24:31.670
- You okay?
- Yeah.

00:24:31.770 --> 00:24:32.999
I'm sorry.

00:24:33.105 --> 00:24:35.540
I never know what
to say at these things.

00:24:35.641 --> 00:24:37.132
Oh, it's okay.

00:24:37.242 --> 00:24:39.507
I'll come by, and we
can discuss the details...

00:24:39.611 --> 00:24:41.978
Construction plans,
repairs, all that.

00:24:42.081 --> 00:24:43.081
Yeah.

00:24:43.182 --> 00:24:45.879
Well... when you're ready.

00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:47.248
Okay? Don't rush.

00:24:47.553 --> 00:24:49.181
Just come on by my office.

00:24:49.488 --> 00:24:51.514
- Yeah, thanks, Tom.
- Yeah. Hang in there.

00:24:51.623 --> 00:24:53.592
- Appreciate it.
- Yeah.

00:24:58.764 --> 00:25:00.699
Jude spoke of you all the time.

00:25:00.799 --> 00:25:04.031
His American brother.

00:25:04.136 --> 00:25:07.265
I thank God he wasn't
alone in his last moments.

00:25:08.741 --> 00:25:10.209
I'm sorry.

00:25:10.509 --> 00:25:12.705
This is not your fault.

00:25:12.811 --> 00:25:18.546
God... He uses all
things for His good.

00:25:18.650 --> 00:25:20.551
You know this.

00:25:29.695 --> 00:25:31.561
What does...?

00:25:31.663 --> 00:25:34.258
I think that's what
Jude said to me.

00:25:34.566 --> 00:25:36.296
Last thing he said to me.

00:25:36.602 --> 00:25:38.594
Wh-What does that mean?

00:25:38.704 --> 00:25:41.799
It's hard to translate.

00:25:41.907 --> 00:25:45.639
In English, it
means basically...

00:25:45.744 --> 00:25:49.010
"Always God is good.

00:25:49.114 --> 00:25:53.677
And God is good always."

00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:39.826
Hey.

00:26:39.932 --> 00:26:42.128
Dave, what are you doing here?

00:26:43.635 --> 00:26:44.898
Well, it's Saturday, isn't it?

00:26:45.003 --> 00:26:47.734
I mean, people
still need to eat.

00:26:47.840 --> 00:26:49.880
Sorry, it's a little bit
light this week, but, uh...

00:26:49.942 --> 00:26:52.605
well, everything in the
pantry was ruined, so...

00:26:52.711 --> 00:26:54.202
I know. I heard. I'm so sorry.

00:26:54.313 --> 00:26:55.872
And Jude.

00:26:55.981 --> 00:26:58.075
Oh, I can't believe it.

00:26:58.183 --> 00:27:00.118
Thanks.

00:27:00.219 --> 00:27:01.812
I'll be okay.

00:27:01.920 --> 00:27:03.149
You hungry?

00:27:03.255 --> 00:27:05.281
How about I feed
you for a change?

00:27:05.390 --> 00:27:08.019
Thanks, but, uh...

00:27:08.127 --> 00:27:09.151
rain check?

00:27:09.261 --> 00:27:10.889
Okay.

00:27:10.996 --> 00:27:13.090
You know where to find me.

00:27:25.844 --> 00:27:26.937
Hey.

00:27:27.045 --> 00:27:28.638
Dave.

00:27:28.747 --> 00:27:31.273
Thanks for coming in.

00:27:31.383 --> 00:27:33.682
Let's go get a cup of coffee.

00:27:33.785 --> 00:27:35.344
Sure.

00:27:35.654 --> 00:27:38.317
Tom, this is insane.

00:27:38.423 --> 00:27:40.324
You're gonna use
this as an opportunity

00:27:40.425 --> 00:27:42.917
to advance some
political agenda?

00:27:43.028 --> 00:27:44.326
It's not about that.

00:27:44.429 --> 00:27:45.954
You don't just
knock a church down

00:27:46.064 --> 00:27:47.794
because of a little controversy.

00:27:47.900 --> 00:27:50.028
Look, the insurance
will cover the damage.

00:27:50.135 --> 00:27:51.660
It won't cost the
university anything.

00:27:51.770 --> 00:27:53.864
It's not about
the money, either.

00:27:53.972 --> 00:27:55.702
It's really not.

00:27:55.807 --> 00:27:57.275
This makes no sense.

00:27:57.376 --> 00:27:59.368
We were attacked.

00:27:59.678 --> 00:28:01.670
I know.

00:28:01.780 --> 00:28:04.375
But, Dave, we're
worried about the school,

00:28:04.683 --> 00:28:06.083
the welfare of the students.

00:28:06.185 --> 00:28:08.177
There are a lot of factors here.

00:28:09.788 --> 00:28:11.723
Look, I know you're upset.

00:28:11.823 --> 00:28:13.416
You have every right to be.

00:28:13.725 --> 00:28:15.091
I don't like this, either.

00:28:15.194 --> 00:28:16.856
I hope you get that.

00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:21.864
It's all in there.

00:28:28.006 --> 00:28:30.237
This was my father's church.

00:28:32.144 --> 00:28:34.306
I was baptized there.

00:28:34.413 --> 00:28:36.939
I spent my whole life there.

00:28:37.049 --> 00:28:38.381
I know.

00:28:38.483 --> 00:28:40.008
It's my home, Tom.

00:28:40.118 --> 00:28:41.848
It's everything I have.

00:28:43.956 --> 00:28:45.288
And it's not for sale.

00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:47.359
I don't think you're
hearing me, Dave.

00:28:47.459 --> 00:28:50.725
The board has decided.

00:28:50.829 --> 00:28:52.923
It's a done deal.

00:28:55.934 --> 00:28:57.869
I'm sorry.

00:28:57.970 --> 00:28:59.802
<i>This is absurd.</i>

00:28:59.905 --> 00:29:01.385
<i>They can just take
the church from us?</i>

00:29:01.440 --> 00:29:03.841
- I mean, don't we own this land?
- Yes.

00:29:03.942 --> 00:29:06.275
- So, how is this legal?
- Eminent domain.

00:29:06.378 --> 00:29:08.847
I studied property law
a bit in grad school.

00:29:08.947 --> 00:29:11.314
As I understand it, the state
gave all public universities

00:29:11.416 --> 00:29:13.783
complete autonomy
over eminent domain.

00:29:13.885 --> 00:29:16.411
Which means Hadleigh
can legally force us to sell.

00:29:16.521 --> 00:29:18.353
- Where are we supposed to go?
- And with what

00:29:18.457 --> 00:29:20.201
they're offering, how can
we build anything anyway?

00:29:20.225 --> 00:29:21.785
- Can we go to court?
- Another lawsuit?

00:29:21.860 --> 00:29:23.761
- Really?
- I hate to be the bearer of bad news,

00:29:23.862 --> 00:29:26.102
but we've burned through any
legal reserves and then some

00:29:26.198 --> 00:29:28.638
- over the last few months.
- No land within 30 miles of here.

00:29:28.800 --> 00:29:30.178
We're out of money,
plain and simple.

00:29:30.202 --> 00:29:31.363
None that we can afford.

00:29:31.470 --> 00:29:33.837
I don't see that we
have an option here.

00:29:38.410 --> 00:29:40.106
You gonna be okay?

00:29:45.317 --> 00:29:50.255
All these years this
church has been here.

00:29:50.355 --> 00:29:53.883
When I think about the
work that God has done

00:29:53.992 --> 00:29:56.826
and the lives that
He's changed...

00:29:58.230 --> 00:30:00.131
Now it's just a crime scene.

00:30:08.373 --> 00:30:11.309
You know, Keaton
stopped by the other day.

00:30:11.410 --> 00:30:13.276
Remember her?

00:30:13.378 --> 00:30:17.008
First time I've seen
her in five months.

00:30:17.115 --> 00:30:19.016
She's lost.

00:30:19.117 --> 00:30:21.951
She needs someone to walk
with her right where she's at.

00:30:22.054 --> 00:30:24.046
There are hundreds
more like her.

00:30:24.156 --> 00:30:26.921
- Here.
- I know, Josh. I got it, but...

00:30:27.025 --> 00:30:28.536
This is why I took on
Professor Radisson,

00:30:28.560 --> 00:30:30.859
why I left law school
for this ministry.

00:30:30.962 --> 00:30:34.399
Because what we do
and how we do it, it...

00:30:34.499 --> 00:30:36.092
it's important, Dave.

00:30:36.201 --> 00:30:38.466
Josh, we have no
money, no lawyers.

00:30:38.570 --> 00:30:40.129
If I could do
something, I would.

00:30:40.238 --> 00:30:42.139
It's just... it's not that easy.

00:30:43.275 --> 00:30:45.141
No, it's not easy.

00:30:46.244 --> 00:30:48.372
But it's simple.

00:30:50.549 --> 00:30:52.108
Look, I, uh...

00:30:52.217 --> 00:30:55.312
I hate to quote
scripture to a pastor,

00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:57.184
but, um...

00:30:57.289 --> 00:30:59.588
you remember Luke 12:48?

00:31:02.027 --> 00:31:03.325
Seems like you're the one

00:31:03.428 --> 00:31:05.090
much is being
asked of this time.

00:31:08.266 --> 00:31:12.101
If you decide you
want to fight this,

00:31:12.204 --> 00:31:14.901
pretty sure God will
handle the details.

00:31:16.241 --> 00:31:18.540
And I'll be right
here beside you.

00:32:16.034 --> 00:32:18.162
<i>You've got an apartment?</i>

00:32:18.270 --> 00:32:20.136
Okay, apartment "E"?

00:32:20.238 --> 00:32:22.707
Thank you.

00:32:23.008 --> 00:32:24.285
Okay, don't you worry about it.

00:32:24.309 --> 00:32:25.607
I know. Thank you, Pearce.

00:32:25.710 --> 00:32:27.269
I swear Mike's a good kid.

00:32:27.379 --> 00:32:29.457
He's just really struggling
right now, with his friends.

00:32:29.481 --> 00:32:31.507
- He's just caught up...
- What are you doing here?

00:32:38.957 --> 00:32:41.085
Dad's church.

00:32:41.193 --> 00:32:43.992
You'd hardly even recognize it.

00:32:44.095 --> 00:32:46.360
Hey, look, this is a
property law case.

00:32:46.465 --> 00:32:48.127
It's not really my thing.

00:32:48.233 --> 00:32:50.395
Pearce, you're a
social justice attorney.

00:32:50.502 --> 00:32:52.246
They're forcing us out
because we're a church.

00:32:52.270 --> 00:32:54.205
This is exactly your thing.

00:32:56.308 --> 00:32:58.436
Let me get this
straight... You drive

00:32:58.543 --> 00:33:00.273
all the way up here,
you don't even call.

00:33:00.378 --> 00:33:02.006
Were you afraid I'd say no?

00:33:02.113 --> 00:33:04.673
I didn't know what
you'd say, to be honest.

00:33:04.983 --> 00:33:06.975
Look, I have a little money.

00:33:07.085 --> 00:33:08.644
I don't want your money.

00:33:08.753 --> 00:33:10.551
This is a legit offer.

00:33:10.655 --> 00:33:12.180
Thing goes to trial,

00:33:12.290 --> 00:33:14.035
jury will probably give
you half that amount.

00:33:14.059 --> 00:33:15.254
Less even.

00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:16.760
Money aside...

00:33:17.062 --> 00:33:19.054
these things always get messy.

00:33:20.198 --> 00:33:22.292
God called me to fight.

00:33:22.400 --> 00:33:24.426
I'm gonna fight.

00:33:24.536 --> 00:33:27.301
Aw... God calls
you, you call me.

00:33:29.374 --> 00:33:31.252
- Did you see that? Uh-huh.
- Right in the third position.

00:33:31.276 --> 00:33:33.040
Third position?

00:33:35.013 --> 00:33:36.675
Adam, what's up,
baby? Where you been?

00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:42.253
Can I talk to you?

00:33:57.335 --> 00:33:59.133
What do I do?

00:34:00.472 --> 00:34:02.065
What do I do?

00:34:03.341 --> 00:34:05.333
I don't know what to do.

00:34:14.119 --> 00:34:16.145
<i>Hey, I appreciate
you coming down.</i>

00:34:16.254 --> 00:34:18.314
<i>I know you're
busy. It's a lot to ask.</i>

00:34:18.423 --> 00:34:19.755
<i>Sure.</i>

00:34:26.531 --> 00:34:27.760
Wow. Look at this place.

00:34:28.066 --> 00:34:29.557
It got smaller.

00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:35.366
What'd you do to the tree?

00:34:35.473 --> 00:34:37.305
Huh?

00:34:37.409 --> 00:34:39.537
What's wrong with it?

00:34:39.644 --> 00:34:41.636
For one thing, it's dead.

00:34:44.449 --> 00:34:47.385
I figured you could
take your old room.

00:34:47.485 --> 00:34:51.115
It's kind of a guest room
and some storage, but...

00:34:52.857 --> 00:34:54.689
Wow.

00:34:54.793 --> 00:34:57.285
Got the old man's chair.

00:34:57.395 --> 00:34:59.591
Allowed to sit in it now?

00:35:09.708 --> 00:35:12.143
Sorry to hear about your friend.

00:35:12.243 --> 00:35:14.769
Yeah. Thanks.

00:35:14.879 --> 00:35:16.745
I'm okay.

00:35:19.117 --> 00:35:20.608
You know, that's...

00:35:20.719 --> 00:35:23.712
what you said at Mom's
funeral: "I'm okay."

00:35:23.822 --> 00:35:26.348
Somebody burns your church down,

00:35:26.458 --> 00:35:28.654
kills your friend,
but you're okay.

00:35:28.760 --> 00:35:30.854
What do you want
me to say, Pearce?

00:35:31.162 --> 00:35:32.858
Yes, I'm having a hard time.

00:35:33.164 --> 00:35:35.224
Just doing my
best to get through.

00:35:36.501 --> 00:35:37.621
You want something to drink?

00:35:37.669 --> 00:35:39.160
You got booze?

00:35:39.270 --> 00:35:40.738
No.

00:35:49.147 --> 00:35:51.412
Did you buy three
boxes of these for me?

00:35:51.516 --> 00:35:52.609
Of course.

00:35:52.717 --> 00:35:54.549
I knew you'd come.

00:35:54.653 --> 00:35:57.282
Unfortunately, I don't
really eat Zingers anymore.

00:35:57.389 --> 00:35:58.899
What do you mean,
you don't eat Zingers?

00:35:58.923 --> 00:35:59.923
You love those things.

00:36:00.191 --> 00:36:01.386
What happened?

00:36:01.493 --> 00:36:02.859
Triple bypass.

00:36:03.161 --> 00:36:04.561
Heart surgery?

00:36:04.663 --> 00:36:06.256
You had heart surgery?

00:36:06.364 --> 00:36:09.198
- Six years ago.
- I had no idea.

00:36:09.300 --> 00:36:10.791
Why would you?

00:36:12.604 --> 00:36:14.630
Well, we're all caught up.

00:36:14.739 --> 00:36:17.299
And I'm gonna
hit the hay. Night.

00:36:18.910 --> 00:36:20.606
Night.

00:36:34.192 --> 00:36:36.237
Eminent domain precedent cases

00:36:36.261 --> 00:36:38.787
having to do with churches
specifically would be best.

00:36:38.897 --> 00:36:41.196
I'll be back as soon as I can.

00:36:41.299 --> 00:36:43.495
Well, just take the
meeting without me, Todd.

00:36:43.601 --> 00:36:45.797
No, I realize that,
but it's a family thing.

00:36:45.904 --> 00:36:48.499
What do you want me to say?

00:36:48.606 --> 00:36:50.541
Just make sure everything
has the same zip.

00:36:50.642 --> 00:36:52.508
Okay? Okay, thanks.

00:36:52.610 --> 00:36:54.238
Make yourself at home.

00:36:54.345 --> 00:36:56.610
- You doing all right?
- I'll tell you what.

00:36:56.715 --> 00:36:58.707
You stop asking me, and
I'll stop saying I'm okay.

00:36:58.817 --> 00:37:00.410
Fair enough.

00:37:01.753 --> 00:37:03.654
Ready to get to it?

00:37:03.755 --> 00:37:06.452
I've been getting
to it since 5:00 a.m.

00:37:06.558 --> 00:37:08.652
Okay? I'm starving.
There's nothing in that fridge

00:37:08.760 --> 00:37:11.662
but moldy casseroles.
Is Doe's still open?

00:37:11.763 --> 00:37:13.629
- I guess.
- Well, let's go.

00:37:13.732 --> 00:37:14.995
Don't eat that.

00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:18.733
<i>The government
takes private property.</i>

00:37:18.837 --> 00:37:19.896
<i>They do it all the time.</i>

00:37:20.004 --> 00:37:21.666
End of story.

00:37:21.773 --> 00:37:24.436
How do you think highways
and railroads get built, man?

00:37:24.542 --> 00:37:26.272
But this isn't about a railroad.

00:37:26.377 --> 00:37:29.006
They said they need the land
to build a new student union.

00:37:29.314 --> 00:37:30.543
I hardly think that qualifies.

00:37:30.648 --> 00:37:31.877
We'll see. It might.

00:37:31.983 --> 00:37:33.884
You're not hearing me.

00:37:33.985 --> 00:37:35.629
They just want the church
gone because they think

00:37:35.653 --> 00:37:37.679
it's bad PR for the university.

00:37:37.789 --> 00:37:39.280
Yeah, they're probably right.

00:37:39.390 --> 00:37:41.291
- Pearce.
- Hey, listen, man.

00:37:41.392 --> 00:37:43.793
I said this ain't my thing.

00:37:43.895 --> 00:37:45.557
All right? Now
you want to tell me

00:37:45.663 --> 00:37:47.063
how to fight an
eminent domain case?

00:37:47.332 --> 00:37:48.493
Why don't I just go home?

00:37:48.600 --> 00:37:49.693
You can do it.

00:38:01.780 --> 00:38:03.715
This is eerie.

00:38:06.618 --> 00:38:08.746
Let's go check it out.

00:38:08.853 --> 00:38:10.822
Can't. It's all locked up.

00:38:33.077 --> 00:38:34.807
Last time I was
in this building,

00:38:34.913 --> 00:38:36.814
Dad was standing right there.

00:38:57.368 --> 00:38:58.802
Hey.

00:39:00.471 --> 00:39:03.407
You got in so much
trouble for that.

00:39:04.976 --> 00:39:06.842
So stupid.

00:39:10.648 --> 00:39:12.981
I'm gonna write a letter
to the board of trustees

00:39:13.084 --> 00:39:15.713
and introduce myself
as your legal counsel.

00:39:15.820 --> 00:39:19.814
I'll politely let them know we
won't be entertaining any more

00:39:19.924 --> 00:39:23.588
backroom offers
between old friends.

00:39:26.898 --> 00:39:28.594
Thank you.

00:39:29.834 --> 00:39:32.463
One step at a
time, little brother.

00:39:34.105 --> 00:39:36.006
<i>His brother is a lawyer?</i>

00:39:36.107 --> 00:39:37.507
Are you kidding me?

00:39:37.609 --> 00:39:39.009
Of course he's gonna fight back.

00:39:39.110 --> 00:39:40.840
What'd you expect?

00:39:40.945 --> 00:39:43.938
At least we can offer him
a... a better settlement.

00:39:44.048 --> 00:39:45.710
Something more fair.

00:39:45.817 --> 00:39:47.581
And where do we
take that money from?

00:39:47.685 --> 00:39:49.125
To pay any more
than legally required

00:39:49.153 --> 00:39:50.712
is a disservice to the school.

00:39:50.822 --> 00:39:53.553
Not to mention, it's unethical.

00:39:53.658 --> 00:39:56.127
Be careful not to
let your friendship

00:39:56.427 --> 00:39:58.419
with Reverend Dave
cloud your judgment.

00:39:58.529 --> 00:40:01.124
Look, I'm on your side.

00:40:01.432 --> 00:40:04.664
My advice is take
care of this now.

00:40:04.769 --> 00:40:07.136
Or the person who
replaces you will.

00:40:11.542 --> 00:40:13.053
<i>And it's important to remember,</i>

00:40:13.077 --> 00:40:14.602
<i>in the midst of all
this controversy,</i>

00:40:14.712 --> 00:40:16.442
<i>that friends and
family are now grieving</i>

00:40:16.547 --> 00:40:18.516
<i>the death of this innocent man</i>

00:40:18.616 --> 00:40:21.108
<i>killed in this tragic
and senseless way.</i>

00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:22.910
<i>I can't even imagine
the heartbreak</i>

00:40:23.021 --> 00:40:24.717
<i>for his parents having to...</i>

00:40:40.071 --> 00:40:41.937
<i>Maybe you just need to stop</i>

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:45.442
- thinking about it.
- I can't.

00:40:45.543 --> 00:40:47.068
How can I?

00:40:48.579 --> 00:40:51.048
Everybody thinks...

00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:54.142
that he was...

00:40:54.452 --> 00:40:56.717
murdered.

00:40:56.821 --> 00:41:01.054
His... his friends,
his... his parents.

00:41:01.159 --> 00:41:02.718
They deserve to
know the truth...

00:41:02.827 --> 00:41:04.227
That it was an accident.

00:41:04.529 --> 00:41:07.499
Maybe it'll help them.

00:41:07.598 --> 00:41:09.543
Maybe that'll... that'll
give them some sort of...

00:41:09.567 --> 00:41:10.899
- But...
- closure.

00:41:11.002 --> 00:41:14.905
- I don't know.
- Okay, okay, so say you confess.

00:41:15.006 --> 00:41:17.669
Maybe they'll go
easy on you, but...

00:41:17.775 --> 00:41:19.004
maybe they won't.

00:41:19.110 --> 00:41:21.477
Okay, and then what?

00:41:23.081 --> 00:41:25.209
I don't know.

00:41:30.088 --> 00:41:32.023
Do you really believe...

00:41:33.091 --> 00:41:35.686
that there's a God?

00:41:40.698 --> 00:41:42.496
I don't know.

00:41:42.600 --> 00:41:44.125
I guess.

00:41:46.804 --> 00:41:48.898
If He does exist...

00:41:52.176 --> 00:41:54.941
do you think that
He would forgive me?

00:41:58.583 --> 00:42:00.245
Of course.

00:42:21.572 --> 00:42:23.871
Hey, Pearce, I'm
headed to church.

00:42:23.975 --> 00:42:25.102
You want to join?

00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:27.007
Not one bit.

00:42:30.815 --> 00:42:32.181
Look what I found.

00:42:32.283 --> 00:42:33.842
What?

00:42:34.986 --> 00:42:36.249
Check it out.

00:42:36.554 --> 00:42:37.920
My gosh.

00:42:38.022 --> 00:42:40.218
Wait, wait, wait. I want
to show you something.

00:42:40.324 --> 00:42:41.917
Oh, man.

00:42:51.002 --> 00:42:53.562
Stretchy!

00:42:53.671 --> 00:42:56.106
Wow.

00:42:56.207 --> 00:42:57.698
I thought most of this stuff

00:42:57.809 --> 00:42:59.573
would've ended up in a landfill.

00:42:59.677 --> 00:43:01.305
- No.
- Hey.

00:43:03.247 --> 00:43:05.648
Pearce, Aunt Celia painted that.

00:43:05.750 --> 00:43:07.651
Who cares? It's ugly.

00:43:07.752 --> 00:43:10.017
- Bet you can't hit the frog.
- Grow up.

00:43:10.121 --> 00:43:11.851
Ten bucks.

00:43:11.956 --> 00:43:13.754
Give it to me.

00:43:18.996 --> 00:43:20.624
Told you.

00:43:24.235 --> 00:43:27.763
Wow. Mandy Stebbins.

00:43:27.872 --> 00:43:30.637
- Whatever happened to her?
- I don't know.

00:43:30.741 --> 00:43:32.733
If she's not on
Facebook, I have no idea.

00:43:33.845 --> 00:43:34.845
Hey.

00:43:36.714 --> 00:43:38.683
Confirmation.

00:43:40.118 --> 00:43:41.882
You still pray for me?

00:43:41.986 --> 00:43:43.887
Pearce, can we not?

00:43:43.988 --> 00:43:46.617
Why? I'm just curious.

00:43:47.859 --> 00:43:50.021
Yeah. Sometimes.

00:43:50.128 --> 00:43:51.152
I knew it.

00:43:51.262 --> 00:43:52.890
What do you pray for?

00:43:52.997 --> 00:43:55.057
I'll come back around,
I'll find peace? What?

00:43:55.166 --> 00:43:57.211
- Is this fun for you?
- I'm just making conversation.

00:43:57.235 --> 00:43:58.931
Yeah, well, maybe
I'll pray that you make

00:43:59.036 --> 00:44:01.870
better conversation.

00:44:01.973 --> 00:44:03.635
Josh?

00:44:03.741 --> 00:44:06.176
Wha...? Right now?

00:44:08.746 --> 00:44:10.772
Hey, I'm gonna need the name

00:44:10.882 --> 00:44:12.192
- of a circuit judge down here.
- Whoa. -Whoa.

00:44:12.216 --> 00:44:14.242
Yes. Now. Today.

00:44:14.352 --> 00:44:16.014
- Okay, let me know.
- Dave! -Yeah.

00:44:16.120 --> 00:44:18.419
- What... what's going on?
- They won't stop.

00:44:18.723 --> 00:44:20.089
Excuse me. Excuse me.

00:44:20.191 --> 00:44:21.784
Hey. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:44:21.893 --> 00:44:23.794
- Stop! Stop!
- Hey. I need you on the other

00:44:23.895 --> 00:44:26.106
- side of the tape, sir.
- I'm the pastor of this church.

00:44:26.130 --> 00:44:27.962
Well, that may
be, but it's not safe.

00:44:28.065 --> 00:44:29.985
- It's okay. I'm his attorney.
- Congratulations.

00:44:30.067 --> 00:44:32.229
And I'm a Mets fan.
Now, move back,

00:44:32.336 --> 00:44:34.328
- or I call the cops.
- Already called 'em.

00:44:34.438 --> 00:44:35.997
Hey, buddy, I have
a demo permit.

00:44:36.107 --> 00:44:38.235
You got a permit to wreck
a church on a Sunday?

00:44:38.342 --> 00:44:39.386
- Really?
- Yeah, what can I say?

00:44:39.410 --> 00:44:41.021
Signed by the president
of the university.

00:44:41.045 --> 00:44:42.775
"Thomas Ellsworth."

00:44:42.880 --> 00:44:45.145
- Unbelievable.
- Just trying to do my job here.

00:44:45.249 --> 00:44:47.718
Yeah, and I'm trying to do
mine. Give me your keys.

00:44:47.818 --> 00:44:49.396
You touch this church
before I get back, I'll have you

00:44:49.420 --> 00:44:51.355
arrested for destruction
of property, okay?

00:44:51.455 --> 00:44:52.684
You stay put.

00:44:52.790 --> 00:44:54.070
Yeah, what do you want me to do?

00:44:54.158 --> 00:44:55.158
I don't know. Stall.

00:44:57.929 --> 00:45:00.330
- You have a Bible?
- Yeah.

00:45:01.866 --> 00:45:03.143
<i>Yeah, yeah, Gloria Pascual.</i>

00:45:03.167 --> 00:45:04.167
<i>I know.</i>

00:45:04.202 --> 00:45:05.795
I'm already on my way.

00:45:06.971 --> 00:45:09.099
What? Are you kidding me?

00:45:12.009 --> 00:45:13.409
Of course she is. It's Sunday.

00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:14.735
Where is she?

00:45:14.845 --> 00:45:16.108
<i>Yeah, yeah, I know it.</i>

00:45:16.214 --> 00:45:17.842
<i>I know it.</i>

00:45:17.949 --> 00:45:19.178
<i>Hey, everyone.</i>

00:45:19.283 --> 00:45:20.979
We're gonna hold service.

00:45:21.085 --> 00:45:22.849
Right now.

00:45:22.954 --> 00:45:23.994
Come on in, guys. Come on.

00:45:24.021 --> 00:45:25.751
Come on over here.

00:45:25.856 --> 00:45:27.188
Can I have that Bible?

00:45:27.291 --> 00:45:28.384
Yeah, yeah.

00:45:28.492 --> 00:45:29.926
Said some kind of lawyer.

00:45:30.027 --> 00:45:31.393
So the, uh...

00:45:31.495 --> 00:45:35.125
the Bible is the Word of God.

00:45:35.233 --> 00:45:38.294
But how often do we
really take time to read it?

00:45:38.402 --> 00:45:40.132
Let's start at the
top, shall we?

00:45:40.238 --> 00:45:42.798
- "In the beginning..."
- Oh, man.

00:45:42.907 --> 00:45:44.808
<i>They haven't even filed yet.</i>

00:45:44.909 --> 00:45:47.003
<i>No appraisals, no
escrow deposits.</i>

00:45:47.111 --> 00:45:48.909
<i>It's an old-fashioned
end around.</i>

00:45:49.013 --> 00:45:50.504
Hold on.

00:45:52.984 --> 00:45:55.886
You still there? You still
gotta send me the injunction.

00:45:55.987 --> 00:45:57.387
Yeah, PDF's fine.

00:45:57.488 --> 00:45:59.013
Okay, hurry up.

00:45:59.123 --> 00:46:00.819
Hey, hey, hey! I-I
don't even know

00:46:00.925 --> 00:46:02.325
what she looks like.

00:46:02.426 --> 00:46:04.861
The judge! Who do you
think I'm talking about?

00:46:04.962 --> 00:46:07.022
Yeah, send me a pic.

00:46:32.123 --> 00:46:33.989
<i>"The serpent</i>

00:46:34.091 --> 00:46:35.992
"was more crafty than
any of the wild animals

00:46:36.093 --> 00:46:37.356
"the Lord God had made.

00:46:37.461 --> 00:46:38.952
"And he said to the woman,

00:46:39.063 --> 00:46:40.998
"" Did God really
say you must not eat

00:46:41.098 --> 00:46:43.043
from the tree in any garden? ""

00:46:52.310 --> 00:46:55.508
Your Honor, I am so
sorry, but I'm an attorney,

00:46:55.813 --> 00:46:57.509
and it's important
that I speak with you.

00:46:57.815 --> 00:47:00.910
I'm in the middle of Mass.

00:47:01.018 --> 00:47:04.045
I'm aware. It's...
it's very timely.

00:47:04.155 --> 00:47:05.521
It involves a church.

00:47:05.823 --> 00:47:07.314
<i>And we want to take you</i>

00:47:07.425 --> 00:47:08.984
live to the scene right now,

00:47:09.093 --> 00:47:11.221
show you what is
developing as we speak.

00:47:11.329 --> 00:47:13.006
<i>You are looking here
at Saint James Church.</i>

