Just take a look at
their dilemma here.

00:48:16.961 --> 00:48:18.401
This is no longer
a Christian school.

00:48:18.496 --> 00:48:20.296
The church really should
have moved off campus

00:48:20.364 --> 00:48:23.163
50 years ago when the
state bought the university.

00:48:23.267 --> 00:48:25.930
Instead, funding is
given disproportionately

00:48:26.036 --> 00:48:27.504
to one religious organization

00:48:27.605 --> 00:48:29.369
while other ones
are being denied.

00:48:29.473 --> 00:48:32.966
So you add that to all of this
controversy and now violence.

00:48:33.077 --> 00:48:35.273
You tell me... How
can they justify

00:48:35.379 --> 00:48:37.314
keeping the church on campus?

00:48:37.415 --> 00:48:40.408
Thomas Ellsworth is
making the right choice here.

00:48:40.518 --> 00:48:43.454
It's not the easy one,
but it is the right choice.

00:48:43.554 --> 00:48:46.046
<i>I think their intentions
are pretty clear.</i>

00:48:46.157 --> 00:48:48.422
Enough with writing
letters. Let's call 'em out.

00:48:48.526 --> 00:48:50.427
Call 'em out on what, stupidity?

00:48:50.528 --> 00:48:51.928
Why are you so
reluctant to accept

00:48:52.029 --> 00:48:53.573
- what's really going on?
- Unbelievable.

00:48:53.597 --> 00:48:56.260
You guys love to play
the victim card, don't you?

00:48:56.367 --> 00:48:58.063
- "You guys."
- Look, forget it.

00:48:58.169 --> 00:49:00.331
I'm not engaging in a
false narrative with you.

00:49:00.438 --> 00:49:02.066
I'm just... I'm not.

00:49:02.173 --> 00:49:03.483
It undermines true
religious liberty.

00:49:03.507 --> 00:49:05.703
You're talking to a
guy who went to jail

00:49:06.010 --> 00:49:07.187
who's now having
his church stolen.

00:49:07.211 --> 00:49:08.321
How is that false narrative?

00:49:08.345 --> 00:49:10.075
Because it's never that simple.

00:49:10.181 --> 00:49:13.242
The Christian Church has a
long history of persecuting people,

00:49:13.350 --> 00:49:14.682
and then those people push back,

00:49:14.985 --> 00:49:17.250
and you guys want to cry victim.

00:49:17.354 --> 00:49:19.050
And for every example of someone

00:49:19.156 --> 00:49:21.455
who's misrepresented
Jesus for some twisted reason,

00:49:21.559 --> 00:49:24.256
there are a hundred others
who have done good in His name.

00:49:24.361 --> 00:49:26.421
We can debate
history all you want,

00:49:26.530 --> 00:49:29.591
but I'm talking about now,
about getting my church back.

00:49:29.700 --> 00:49:31.532
Can you just help me do that?

00:49:31.635 --> 00:49:33.331
I'm right here, aren't I?

00:49:33.437 --> 00:49:35.633
Just don't drag me into
your personal crusade.

00:49:38.476 --> 00:49:39.705
Where you going?

00:49:40.010 --> 00:49:41.376
I'm going to bed.

00:49:46.050 --> 00:49:47.294
- Thank you, Pastor.
- Thank you for your sacrifice.

00:49:47.318 --> 00:49:48.438
- Appreciate it.
- Thank you.

00:49:48.486 --> 00:49:49.647
Okay.

00:49:51.021 --> 00:49:52.387
Okay.

00:49:56.627 --> 00:49:58.027
Pastor Dave.

00:49:59.196 --> 00:50:00.687
Keaton, how are you?

00:50:00.998 --> 00:50:02.330
I'm okay.

00:50:02.433 --> 00:50:04.334
So, how's stuff going
with the the church?

00:50:04.435 --> 00:50:06.495
Have they found
the person who did it?

00:50:06.604 --> 00:50:08.698
Not yet. They're
still investigating.

00:50:09.006 --> 00:50:12.204
Oh, I just figured, like,
fingerprints or whatever.

00:50:12.309 --> 00:50:14.710
Oh, it's not quite
like the movies.

00:50:15.012 --> 00:50:18.107
It takes time, but I'm
sure they'll catch 'em.

00:50:18.215 --> 00:50:21.151
What's gonna happen
when they find 'em?

00:50:21.252 --> 00:50:25.519
Put 'em away, I
hope, for a long time.

00:50:28.058 --> 00:50:30.084
<i>The order's good
for three weeks.</i>

00:50:30.194 --> 00:50:32.129
Can't be much longer than that.

00:50:32.229 --> 00:50:33.697
Hey, what do you want me to say?

00:50:33.797 --> 00:50:35.789
He's my brother.

00:50:36.100 --> 00:50:38.228
Do me a favor...
Send me some briefs

00:50:38.335 --> 00:50:41.772
for <i>Kelo v. New
London</i> and... what else?

00:50:42.072 --> 00:50:44.667
<i>Faith Temple, uh, v. Brighton.</i>

00:50:44.775 --> 00:50:46.073
Okay, thanks.

00:51:10.301 --> 00:51:12.379
Really, take it with you.
It's getting cold out there.

00:51:12.403 --> 00:51:13.427
All right, bye.

00:51:13.537 --> 00:51:15.199
- Thank you.
- Smells good.

00:51:15.306 --> 00:51:17.366
- Mm-hmm. -Smells good.

00:51:17.474 --> 00:51:19.705
Coming to collect
on that rain check.

00:51:21.779 --> 00:51:23.714
You guys close growing up?

00:51:23.814 --> 00:51:27.216
Yeah. That's why it was so hard.

00:51:27.318 --> 00:51:29.219
Pearce was my hero.

00:51:29.320 --> 00:51:31.846
I mean, he had
this strong faith.

00:51:32.156 --> 00:51:34.182
But he was so cool about it.

00:51:34.291 --> 00:51:36.260
He made Christianity cool.

00:51:36.360 --> 00:51:38.226
Yeah, I know the type.

00:51:38.329 --> 00:51:41.231
Went off to law school
when I started college.

00:51:41.332 --> 00:51:42.664
And then something happened.

00:51:42.766 --> 00:51:44.359
I don't know, he changed.

00:51:44.468 --> 00:51:46.130
How?

00:51:46.236 --> 00:51:47.761
Uh...

00:51:47.871 --> 00:51:51.239
I don't know, I guess he
was struggling in his faith.

00:51:51.342 --> 00:51:53.277
But it was more
than just confusion.

00:51:53.377 --> 00:51:55.471
It was darker than that.

00:51:55.579 --> 00:51:57.343
I always hoped that
he'd come around

00:51:57.448 --> 00:52:00.111
before our parents died.

00:52:01.819 --> 00:52:03.879
It was hard on them.

00:52:04.188 --> 00:52:06.521
Felt like they lost their son.

00:52:06.624 --> 00:52:08.593
You lost your hero.

00:52:08.692 --> 00:52:10.456
Yeah.

00:52:10.561 --> 00:52:12.120
Guess I did.

00:52:15.899 --> 00:52:19.358
That's amazing, isn't it?

00:52:19.470 --> 00:52:20.699
That he can look at that...

00:52:23.374 --> 00:52:25.138
and see that.

00:52:30.314 --> 00:52:32.249
You okay?

00:52:33.817 --> 00:52:36.286
I feel a little bit
like I'm drifting.

00:52:37.655 --> 00:52:39.817
Keep trying to tell
myself all the things

00:52:39.923 --> 00:52:43.451
that I would tell others
who are struggling.

00:52:43.560 --> 00:52:45.358
It's not helping.

00:52:45.462 --> 00:52:48.694
Think I might be bad at my job.

00:52:48.799 --> 00:52:50.768
I doubt that.

00:52:50.868 --> 00:52:53.861
I just want to get back
to the way things were.

00:52:55.406 --> 00:52:56.772
How far back is that?

00:52:58.375 --> 00:53:01.368
I mean, going back
doesn't really work.

00:53:01.478 --> 00:53:02.946
And believe me, I've tried.

00:53:03.247 --> 00:53:06.479
I've gone back to
school, gone back home,

00:53:06.583 --> 00:53:09.246
back to brunette.

00:53:09.353 --> 00:53:12.881
But I've never been able to
go back to the way things were.

00:53:14.558 --> 00:53:16.857
I hope you're wrong.

00:53:16.960 --> 00:53:21.227
'Cause if I can't go back,
I don't know where to go.

00:53:30.774 --> 00:53:32.208
Are you doing okay?

00:53:32.309 --> 00:53:33.834
I told you to stop
asking me that.

00:53:33.944 --> 00:53:35.310
Oh, yeah. I forgot.

00:53:35.412 --> 00:53:37.278
<i>So, how much?</i>

00:53:37.381 --> 00:53:39.373
How much what?

00:53:39.483 --> 00:53:41.281
We made you an offer.

00:53:41.385 --> 00:53:44.219
You're here to
counter, so counter.

00:53:44.321 --> 00:53:46.256
Oh, believe me, I wish I could.

00:53:46.356 --> 00:53:47.847
Unfortunately,
despite my counsel,

00:53:47.958 --> 00:53:50.518
my client is not
interested in money.

00:53:50.627 --> 00:53:51.771
So, what is your
client interested in?

00:53:51.795 --> 00:53:53.696
- I want my church back.
- Dave...

00:53:53.797 --> 00:53:54.890
be reasonable.

00:53:54.998 --> 00:53:56.876
Reason went out the window,
Tom, when you brought

00:53:56.900 --> 00:53:58.459
a demolition crew
to my front door.

00:53:58.569 --> 00:53:59.867
Look, a college campus

00:53:59.970 --> 00:54:01.734
is about education,
not religion.

00:54:01.839 --> 00:54:02.898
We've got limited space.

00:54:03.006 --> 00:54:04.668
We need to maximize
it for every student.

00:54:04.775 --> 00:54:06.820
None of that gives you the
right to tear my church down.

00:54:06.844 --> 00:54:09.006
- Well, actually it does.
- Dana, stop.

00:54:09.313 --> 00:54:11.339
We're wasting our time here.

00:54:11.448 --> 00:54:13.679
We both know that this
meeting was simply a courtesy.

00:54:13.784 --> 00:54:15.878
And, Barbara, we appreciate it.

00:54:15.986 --> 00:54:17.614
It's very courteous.

00:54:17.721 --> 00:54:20.589
I get it. It's a
prime piece of land.

00:54:20.691 --> 00:54:23.024
You know what
I'd do if it were me?

00:54:23.327 --> 00:54:25.796
I'd put in a big student center
with a fancy coffee shop.

00:54:25.896 --> 00:54:27.330
The kids would love it.

00:54:27.431 --> 00:54:29.263
I mean, to me,
that's more valuable

00:54:29.366 --> 00:54:31.494
than a dusty old
church. No offense.

00:54:31.602 --> 00:54:33.571
But he knows
how I feel about it.

00:54:33.670 --> 00:54:35.468
Here's the problem.

00:54:35.572 --> 00:54:38.269
What you're doing,
it's against the law.

00:54:38.375 --> 00:54:41.470
'Cause eminent domain
doesn't automatically apply

00:54:41.578 --> 00:54:44.844
just because you guys
don't like his church.

00:54:44.948 --> 00:54:47.349
So, here's my counter.

00:54:47.451 --> 00:54:49.716
Withdraw your claim, or we sue.

00:54:49.820 --> 00:54:52.654
See what a judge
has to say about it.

00:54:52.756 --> 00:54:54.884
We're done.

00:54:58.562 --> 00:55:00.690
This case will never
make it to court.

00:55:13.811 --> 00:55:15.091
They didn't look
worried, Pearce.

00:55:15.312 --> 00:55:16.644
Oh, they are.
That's their job...

00:55:16.747 --> 00:55:18.340
To not look worried.

00:55:18.448 --> 00:55:20.713
Listen, we gotta change
the conversation in the media.

00:55:20.818 --> 00:55:22.878
Okay, we gotta put a
face to the opposition.

00:55:22.986 --> 00:55:25.751
- Tom?
- Yeah, Tom.

00:55:25.856 --> 00:55:27.700
He's the most visible.
He's got the most to lose.

00:55:27.724 --> 00:55:28.724
You okay with that?

00:55:28.759 --> 00:55:30.785
I'll just tell the truth.

00:55:30.894 --> 00:55:33.762
People need to
know what he's doing.

00:55:33.864 --> 00:55:35.833
Good boy. Let's go.

00:55:38.569 --> 00:55:41.095
But Saint James built
Hadleigh University years ago.

00:55:41.405 --> 00:55:43.965
Exactly. So you see
how far this has gone.

00:55:44.074 --> 00:55:46.475
And now, with the
school board's actions,

00:55:46.577 --> 00:55:49.547
we've been given no choice
but to seek a legal solution.

00:55:49.646 --> 00:55:51.424
All of these college
administrators,

00:55:51.448 --> 00:55:53.917
they go on and on
and on about diversity

00:55:54.017 --> 00:55:55.645
and tolerance and inclusion,

00:55:55.752 --> 00:55:57.448
but yet, when
it's asked of them,

00:55:57.554 --> 00:55:59.455
they run you off of campus.

00:55:59.556 --> 00:56:01.650
That doesn't sound very
tolerant or inclusive to me.

00:56:01.758 --> 00:56:03.454
Tom Ellsworth is
trying to strip away

00:56:03.560 --> 00:56:05.240
the foundational
element of this university

00:56:05.429 --> 00:56:08.490
because he believes that
it is no longer convenient.

00:56:08.599 --> 00:56:10.067
But truth isn't
about convenience.

00:56:10.367 --> 00:56:12.359
And faith in God may not be

00:56:12.469 --> 00:56:14.631
as popular on
campus as it once was,

00:56:14.738 --> 00:56:16.366
but people still have a right...

00:56:16.473 --> 00:56:19.966
A fundamental human
right to express their beliefs,

00:56:20.077 --> 00:56:22.603
even in a public square
at a state university.

00:56:22.713 --> 00:56:25.979
If you agree, we're asking that
you make your voices heard.

00:56:26.083 --> 00:56:27.517
Send an e-mail.

00:56:27.618 --> 00:56:29.052
Make a call.

00:56:29.152 --> 00:56:31.644
Let Tom Ellsworth and
the university board know

00:56:31.755 --> 00:56:35.419
that you believe the
church still has value.

00:56:35.525 --> 00:56:37.245
The gauntlet has been thrown.

00:56:37.394 --> 00:56:39.454
And we'll see how
people respond.

00:56:39.563 --> 00:56:41.623
Dude, almost
three million views.

00:56:41.732 --> 00:56:43.894
People are mad. This is good.

00:56:44.001 --> 00:56:45.902
Does this buy us the
leverage we need?

00:56:46.003 --> 00:56:48.996
Well, we'll find
out at the prelim.

00:56:49.106 --> 00:56:51.575
Need the judge to let
us argue the case, but...

00:56:51.675 --> 00:56:53.405
this all helps.

00:56:54.945 --> 00:56:56.709
Nice work.

00:56:57.781 --> 00:56:59.113
Thanks.

00:57:00.684 --> 00:57:01.995
I think it's time for me

00:57:02.019 --> 00:57:03.453
to get back preaching again.

00:57:03.553 --> 00:57:04.831
I'm afraid I'm
getting so caught up

00:57:04.855 --> 00:57:06.050
in all this, I just...

00:57:06.156 --> 00:57:08.091
I don't want to lose sight
of my work, you know.

00:57:08.191 --> 00:57:10.057
Well, let me know
when and where.

00:57:10.160 --> 00:57:12.026
I'll be there for sure.

00:57:12.129 --> 00:57:14.030
Hey, we're back.

00:57:14.131 --> 00:57:16.566
- Oh, I turned it off.
- What?

00:57:16.667 --> 00:57:18.727
Don't you want to see
if they get the diamond?

00:57:20.137 --> 00:57:21.730
Don't you knock?

00:57:21.838 --> 00:57:23.534
- What are you doing?
- I'm on the phone.

00:57:23.640 --> 00:57:24.903
Who you talking to so late?

00:57:25.008 --> 00:57:26.533
None of your business.

00:57:26.643 --> 00:57:28.475
Is that Pearce?
Tell him I said hi.

00:57:28.578 --> 00:57:29.773
Meg says hi.

00:57:29.880 --> 00:57:31.212
Hi, Meg.

00:57:31.515 --> 00:57:32.515
Uh, let me call you back.

00:57:32.582 --> 00:57:34.016
Ooh, what's the deal there?

00:57:34.117 --> 00:57:36.518
There's no deal.
She's a friend of mine.

00:57:36.620 --> 00:57:38.953
She runs one of the
ministries we support.

00:57:40.524 --> 00:57:42.686
- What do you want, Pearce?
- Nothing.

00:57:42.793 --> 00:57:44.762
- Is that my shirt?
- Yeah.

00:58:01.011 --> 00:58:02.912
What are you doing?

00:58:03.013 --> 00:58:05.505
I told you, this tree's dead.
It's gonna fall on the house.

00:58:05.615 --> 00:58:07.174
I didn't ask you to cut it down.

00:58:07.484 --> 00:58:09.646
- I can do it myself.
- Can you, now?

00:58:09.753 --> 00:58:11.051
Yeah, I could.

00:58:11.154 --> 00:58:13.214
Go for it.

00:58:13.523 --> 00:58:14.923
All right, fine.

00:58:19.830 --> 00:58:21.526
You might want to back up.

00:58:24.534 --> 00:58:26.526
- Gotta do better than that.
- It was a warm-up.

00:58:30.674 --> 00:58:32.802
Still warming up?

00:58:40.617 --> 00:58:41.961
Careful with that
weak heart of yours.

00:58:41.985 --> 00:58:43.214
Ha ha. Funny guy.

00:58:43.520 --> 00:58:44.579
Watch this.

00:58:44.688 --> 00:58:46.714
Get ready to yell "timber."

00:58:46.823 --> 00:58:49.088
I got a better idea.

00:58:51.194 --> 00:58:52.890
Oh, now we're talking.

00:58:52.996 --> 00:58:54.020
Yeah!

00:59:04.274 --> 00:59:06.641
- Okay, give it a push.
- All right, hold up.

00:59:06.743 --> 00:59:08.905
- Tell me when you're ready.
- Yeah.

00:59:09.012 --> 00:59:10.173
Go.

00:59:11.548 --> 00:59:13.016
Ah, we almost got it!

00:59:14.584 --> 00:59:16.815
Oh! Yeah!

00:59:19.156 --> 00:59:20.647
Yes!

00:59:25.262 --> 00:59:28.232
Just promise me you'll
plant something new here.

00:59:28.331 --> 00:59:30.232
Mom liked pomegranate trees.

00:59:33.804 --> 00:59:36.706
Do you even believe in
what we're fighting for?

00:59:38.275 --> 00:59:40.904
Do I believe in your right
to keep your church? Yes.

00:59:41.011 --> 00:59:44.675
But the rest of it...
You know the answer.

00:59:44.781 --> 00:59:46.841
So, why help me?

00:59:46.950 --> 00:59:48.748
What do you think
I do for a living?

00:59:48.852 --> 00:59:50.821
Do you think I need to
have the belief system

00:59:50.921 --> 00:59:53.891
of every crackhead I
defend to defend 'em?

00:59:53.990 --> 00:59:55.959
So religion has no value

00:59:56.059 --> 00:59:58.221
except for the
laws that protect it?

00:59:58.328 --> 01:00:00.593
Value? I don't know.

01:00:00.697 --> 01:00:02.359
But people have evolved.

01:00:02.666 --> 01:00:04.760
Science has
replaced superstition.

01:00:04.868 --> 01:00:07.269
Church has outlived
its usefulness.

01:00:07.370 --> 01:00:10.807
- Wow.
- Okay, I don't expect you to agree, but...

01:00:10.907 --> 01:00:12.218
that's okay, 'cause
this is healthy.

01:00:12.242 --> 01:00:13.733
It's a healthy discourse.

01:00:13.844 --> 01:00:15.335
Pearce, people are broken.

01:00:15.645 --> 01:00:17.204
They're-they're... they're lost.

01:00:17.314 --> 01:00:20.716
They're searching...
For meaning, for purpose.

01:00:20.817 --> 01:00:22.945
Oh, church is the answer
to those problems, huh?

01:00:23.053 --> 01:00:24.919
Church is a place
for people to seek.

01:00:25.021 --> 01:00:28.082
To grapple with those
difficult questions.

01:00:28.191 --> 01:00:31.286
To find hope and... and truth.

01:00:32.629 --> 01:00:34.097
And you know that.

01:00:34.197 --> 01:00:36.291
Or at least you used to.

01:00:36.399 --> 01:00:38.800
Why do you need me to agree
with you about everything?

01:00:38.902 --> 01:00:40.768
I'm just your lawyer.

01:00:40.871 --> 01:00:43.067
I didn't come here
to debate religion

01:00:43.173 --> 01:00:44.869
or do your landscaping.

01:00:46.343 --> 01:00:47.971
But, man, you're
my little brother.

01:00:48.078 --> 01:00:51.105
And I don't like to see
people push you around.

01:00:51.214 --> 01:00:53.706
And that's why I'm helping you.

01:00:53.817 --> 01:00:56.412
And right now, that answer's
gotta be good enough for you.

01:00:59.789 --> 01:01:01.314
<i>Now, this whole situation</i>

01:01:01.424 --> 01:01:03.325
brings you to the Cross.

01:01:03.426 --> 01:01:07.420
And the Cross is both
vertical and horizontal.

01:01:07.731 --> 01:01:09.427
Vertical is me and God.

01:01:09.733 --> 01:01:11.827
God and me... My
relationship with Christ.

01:01:11.935 --> 01:01:13.904
The horizontal
part... you and I.

01:01:14.004 --> 01:01:16.303
Sometimes we get so
caught up in the vertical,

01:01:16.406 --> 01:01:19.240
we forget the horizontal,
forget each other.

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:20.674
Yeah, but it's... it's at

01:01:20.777 --> 01:01:21.954
the intersection
where Jesus comes in.

01:01:21.978 --> 01:01:23.708
- Yes.
- That nexus... and that's

01:01:23.813 --> 01:01:26.749
where Paul's words are so
powerful and compelling...

01:01:26.850 --> 01:01:28.910
Even Jews and gentiles
are fellow citizens.

01:01:29.019 --> 01:01:31.989
<i>So, with all the noise and
anger out there right now,</i>

01:01:32.088 --> 01:01:34.114
<i>it's peace that we
have to think about.</i>

01:01:34.224 --> 01:01:35.692
<i>And it's gonna
require one thing,</i>

01:01:35.792 --> 01:01:37.260
<i>and it's gonna
require sacrifice.</i>

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:39.352
<i>At the end of the
day, we can't forget</i>

01:01:39.462 --> 01:01:41.397
<i>that Christ's
forgiveness came about</i>

01:01:41.698 --> 01:01:43.132
<i>via the conduit
of the sacrifice.</i>

01:01:43.233 --> 01:01:46.726
<i>And we are called, believe
it or not, to do the same.</i>

01:01:58.982 --> 01:02:01.042
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:02:03.320 --> 01:02:05.118
How are you?

01:02:06.957 --> 01:02:08.482
Mm, been better.

01:02:14.898 --> 01:02:18.198
Do you know why my
mom divorced my dad?

01:02:21.404 --> 01:02:23.305
He used to beat her.

01:02:25.375 --> 01:02:26.968
I was nine...

01:02:28.278 --> 01:02:30.304
when she left him.

01:02:33.250 --> 01:02:35.219
You know what our church did?

01:02:37.487 --> 01:02:39.456
They called her a sinner.

01:02:41.391 --> 01:02:42.984
They said that if
she married again

01:02:43.093 --> 01:02:45.358
she'd be an adulterer.

01:02:46.830 --> 01:02:48.492
They humiliated her.

01:02:49.933 --> 01:02:52.232
What I remember
most about that time

01:02:52.335 --> 01:02:56.033
is the sound of my mother
crying herself to sleep.

01:02:56.139 --> 01:02:58.370
I'm so sorry. I...

01:03:01.978 --> 01:03:04.538
So yeah, I get angry sometimes.

01:03:06.416 --> 01:03:09.147
But I didn't... I didn't mean
for anybody to get hurt.

01:03:09.252 --> 01:03:11.221
I know you didn't.

01:03:17.894 --> 01:03:20.386
For what it's worth,
I prayed about it.

01:03:22.932 --> 01:03:24.161
And?

01:03:26.569 --> 01:03:29.095
No answer.

01:03:35.145 --> 01:03:36.943
And did you believe him?

01:03:37.047 --> 01:03:38.174
Of course I believed him.

01:03:38.281 --> 01:03:39.374
I was seven years old.

01:03:39.482 --> 01:03:41.178
I believed whatever he told me.

01:03:41.284 --> 01:03:43.844
"Dave, you can
make your own 7 Up.

01:03:43.953 --> 01:03:45.444
"All you need is...

01:03:45.555 --> 01:03:47.524
is just water and salt."

01:03:49.426 --> 01:03:51.070
- And did you drink it?
- It was terrible, obviously.

01:03:51.094 --> 01:03:53.825
But I kept adding
more and more salt,

01:03:53.930 --> 01:03:57.059
just waiting for
those little bubbles.

01:03:57.167 --> 01:03:59.102
Oh, the poor guy.

01:03:59.202 --> 01:04:02.866
He drank the whole bottle...
Two liters of salt water.

01:04:02.972 --> 01:04:04.873
But I gotta hand it to Pearce.

01:04:04.974 --> 01:04:08.172
He, uh... he waited by
my bedside all night long

01:04:08.278 --> 01:04:10.179
to make sure that I didn't die.

01:04:10.280 --> 01:04:13.182
Yeah. That's what brothers
do. They look out for each other.

01:04:13.283 --> 01:04:15.218
- Hear, hear.
- Hear, hear, brother.

01:04:15.318 --> 01:04:16.547
Thank you.

01:04:16.853 --> 01:04:18.253
I really thought
you were gonna die.

01:04:19.889 --> 01:04:22.017
Hadleigh University
is being flooded

01:04:22.125 --> 01:04:24.117
with calls and e-mails
from angry citizens,

01:04:24.227 --> 01:04:27.061
and it seems Chancellor
Ellsworth, well,

01:04:27.163 --> 01:04:28.859
taking the brunt of that anger.

01:04:38.942 --> 01:04:41.411
Kayla's asking for
her bedtime story.

01:04:45.548 --> 01:04:47.574
Don't answer it, Tom.

01:04:53.590 --> 01:04:55.218
Hello?

01:04:56.359 --> 01:04:58.351
Hello!

01:04:58.461 --> 01:05:00.327
Hel... Stop calling me.

01:05:02.565 --> 01:05:04.125
- What was that?
- Stay here, stay here.

01:05:04.200 --> 01:05:05.224
What?

01:05:05.335 --> 01:05:06.928
Daddy!

01:05:07.036 --> 01:05:09.005
Kayla! Come here, baby.

01:05:17.080 --> 01:05:19.174
What was that?

01:05:22.051 --> 01:05:23.485
Go on upstairs.

01:05:24.954 --> 01:05:27.014
It's okay, baby.

01:05:27.123 --> 01:05:28.648
It's okay.

01:05:31.294 --> 01:05:33.490
I'm very proud of you.

01:05:33.596 --> 01:05:35.155
Of me?

01:05:35.265 --> 01:05:37.029
For what?

01:05:37.133 --> 01:05:41.002
I get the feeling fighting's
not really your thing.

01:05:41.104 --> 01:05:43.437
But it's important
what you're doing.

01:05:44.541 --> 01:05:46.032
It's inspiring.

01:05:48.111 --> 01:05:51.172
I was just thinking
about that sculptor

01:05:51.281 --> 01:05:53.443
chiseling away at that rock.

01:05:55.218 --> 01:05:57.653
It's okay to be broken, Dave.

01:05:57.954 --> 01:06:01.049
It means God's
still shaping you.

01:06:01.157 --> 01:06:02.989
I'm honored to be a part of it.

01:06:07.363 --> 01:06:09.958
- Tom?
- I'm getting death threats, Dave.

01:06:10.066 --> 01:06:12.695
Somebody threw a
brick through my window.

01:06:13.002 --> 01:06:15.481
- Okay, just take it easy, okay?
- No, Kayla could've been hurt!

01:06:15.505 --> 01:06:16.881
I don't know anything
about that. I'm sorry.

01:06:16.905 --> 01:06:17.149
No, no.

01:06:17.173 --> 01:06:18.732
- You did this!
- Hey, hey.

01:06:20.243 --> 01:06:21.711
Pearce!

01:06:23.613 --> 01:06:25.343
Hey!

01:06:25.448 --> 01:06:27.110
Get off him!

01:06:31.321 --> 01:06:34.052
You brought the
fight to us, Tom.

01:06:43.333 --> 01:06:45.302
I'll get you some ice.

01:06:47.337 --> 01:06:49.067
You all right?

01:06:49.172 --> 01:06:51.607
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:06:56.346 --> 01:06:58.315
Maybe we should
just call it a night.

01:06:59.382 --> 01:07:00.611
Yeah. Uh...

01:07:00.717 --> 01:07:02.583
I'll just get my stuff.

01:07:10.627 --> 01:07:12.107
I didn't realize Tom
was a psychopath.

01:07:12.195 --> 01:07:14.664
Well, he's just scared.

01:07:16.466 --> 01:07:19.061
Thanks.

01:07:19.168 --> 01:07:21.728
Way to impress
the lady, by the way.

01:07:22.038 --> 01:07:23.768
Well, it's kind of
my signature move.

01:07:24.073 --> 01:07:26.201
Invite a girl over, and then
get punched in the face.

01:07:26.309 --> 01:07:28.141
Works every time.

01:07:28.244 --> 01:07:30.042
Let's see.

01:07:33.082 --> 01:07:34.516
Ow. What'd you do that for?

01:07:36.286 --> 01:07:37.686
You'll be all right.

01:07:41.658 --> 01:07:43.251
Cottonwood Christian Center

01:07:43.359 --> 01:07:44.827
v. Cypress Redevelopment Agency?

01:07:45.128 --> 01:07:46.472
I got that. Give
me something else.

01:07:46.496 --> 01:07:48.040
Hey, I've got
some leftover pizza.

01:07:48.064 --> 01:07:50.158
Yeah.

01:07:51.234 --> 01:07:52.395
Josh, you're a smart kid.

01:07:52.502 --> 01:07:53.782
Why'd you give up on law school?

01:07:54.070 --> 01:07:55.510
Well, I wouldn't
say I gave up on it.

01:07:55.605 --> 01:07:58.200
Um, once I spent time
on a college campus,

01:07:58.308 --> 01:08:00.334
I realized there was
a real need there.

01:08:00.443 --> 01:08:02.555
You know, ministry's just
another way for me to serve.

01:08:02.579 --> 01:08:04.172
What kind of law
were you studying?

01:08:04.280 --> 01:08:07.079
Same as you... civil
rights, social justice.

01:08:07.183 --> 01:08:09.209
Really? 'Cause you
don't strike me as a liberal.

01:08:09.319 --> 01:08:10.787
Give the kid a break.

01:08:11.087 --> 01:08:12.350
- What?
- I don't think

01:08:12.455 --> 01:08:13.615
standing up for the oppressed

01:08:13.690 --> 01:08:15.556
is exclusive to a
political agenda.

01:08:15.658 --> 01:08:17.217
Well, let me ask you this.

01:08:17.327 --> 01:08:19.626
Do you think that
your religious beliefs

01:08:19.729 --> 01:08:21.823
get in the way of
real social change?

01:08:22.131 --> 01:08:24.123
No, my... my beliefs are
the foundation of change.

01:08:24.233 --> 01:08:27.203
The belief that every human
is made in the image of God.

01:08:27.303 --> 01:08:29.423
I mean, Jesus was the
ultimate social justice warrior.

01:08:29.472 --> 01:08:30.952
He said the lives
of children mattered

01:08:31.174 --> 01:08:33.837
and regarded women
with honor and dignity

01:08:34.143 --> 01:08:36.322
in a cultural moment where a
woman's testimony wasn't even

01:08:36.346 --> 01:08:37.871
permissible in a court of law.

01:08:38.181 --> 01:08:39.725
He consistently stood
up for the mistreated

01:08:39.749 --> 01:08:41.650
and the marginalized.

01:08:41.751 --> 01:08:43.515
Well, I've been
doing this a long time,

01:08:43.620 --> 01:08:45.940
and I wish I'd seen those
words put into action more often.

01:08:46.155 --> 01:08:47.384
Yeah. Me, too.

01:08:47.490 --> 01:08:49.152
We're all responsible
for our part,

01:08:49.258 --> 01:08:50.749
but it's grace and then justice,

01:08:50.860 --> 01:08:52.351
not the other way around.

01:08:52.462 --> 01:08:54.488
Whether you serve
the court or the Lord,

01:08:54.597 --> 01:08:57.328
you should follow the
example of Jesus because...

01:08:57.433 --> 01:09:00.130
without grace as
our goal, we're just...

01:09:00.236 --> 01:09:01.436
you know, we're just fighting.

01:09:01.537 --> 01:09:02.766
Amen.

01:09:02.872 --> 01:09:05.137
Let's say grace.

01:09:05.241 --> 01:09:07.574
Dear Lord: Thank
you for this day.

01:09:07.677 --> 01:09:09.441
Thank you for this food.

01:09:09.545 --> 01:09:11.275
Bless it to our bodies,
and forgive Pearce

01:09:11.381 --> 01:09:13.145
for eating before grace.

01:09:13.249 --> 01:09:15.343
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:09:15.451 --> 01:09:17.647
That's not funny.

01:09:19.489 --> 01:09:21.617
<i>So, if the judge
agrees to let us</i>

01:09:21.724 --> 01:09:23.590
<i>go to trial, do we have a shot?</i>

01:09:23.693 --> 01:09:25.559
If we go to trial,
we're gonna win.

01:09:25.662 --> 01:09:27.426
Public's on our side,
jury's on our side.

01:09:27.530 --> 01:09:29.499
- What if the judge says no?
- Then we're done.

01:09:29.599 --> 01:09:31.227
Great.

01:09:32.902 --> 01:09:35.599
- Am I allowed to talk in there?
- Please don't.

01:09:35.705 --> 01:09:37.585
You know, I've been
thinking... I like this Meg.

01:09:37.640 --> 01:09:39.871
She's the good kind
of Christian... authentic.

01:09:40.176 --> 01:09:42.736
You ought to seal the
deal before she gets wise.

01:09:42.845 --> 01:09:44.313
It's not exactly great timing.

01:09:45.782 --> 01:09:47.546
Maybe I don't want
to rush into things.

01:09:47.650 --> 01:09:49.414
Try not to end up
with two ex-wives.

01:09:49.519 --> 01:09:51.385
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

01:09:51.487 --> 01:09:53.319
It's three now.

01:09:53.423 --> 01:09:55.517
Three?

01:09:55.625 --> 01:09:57.436
Hadleigh offered a sum
that's fair market value

01:09:57.460 --> 01:09:59.861
- for the property.
- It's perfectly fair.

01:09:59.962 --> 01:10:03.592
But Saint James' value can't
be measured only in dollars.

01:10:03.700 --> 01:10:05.878
The court has no standard
for determining intrinsic value.

01:10:05.902 --> 01:10:09.236
Your Honor, Saint James
has had a positive impact

01:10:09.338 --> 01:10:10.829
on this community
for generations.

01:10:10.940 --> 01:10:13.774
The university concedes the
plaintiff is not without merit,

01:10:13.876 --> 01:10:16.607
but we question the
relevancy to this case.

01:10:16.713 --> 01:10:17.713
May I say something?

01:10:17.814 --> 01:10:19.749
Well, you brought the lawsuit.

01:10:19.849 --> 01:10:21.818
If you want to assess
the value of the church

01:10:21.918 --> 01:10:24.547
to this community,
just turn on the news.

01:10:24.654 --> 01:10:28.318
The community is
speaking... Loudly.

01:10:29.659 --> 01:10:31.890
<i>This is what victory feels like.</i>

01:10:31.994 --> 01:10:33.826
We're going to court.

01:10:33.930 --> 01:10:35.865
Come on, man, this is a big win.

01:10:35.965 --> 01:10:37.558
Be happy.

01:10:37.667 --> 01:10:39.295
Ow.

01:10:39.402 --> 01:10:40.768
- Be happy!
- Stop it.

01:10:40.870 --> 01:10:41.870
Be happy.

01:10:41.938 --> 01:10:43.463
Ow! Will you just...

01:10:43.573 --> 01:10:45.872
Be happy. Oh!
There's my little brother!

01:10:45.975 --> 01:10:47.807
No, I'm not happy
suing my friend.

01:10:47.910 --> 01:10:49.344
I'm not happy suing anybody.

01:10:49.445 --> 01:10:50.913
Okay.

01:10:51.013 --> 01:10:53.881
Well, number one, Tom
Ellsworth is not your friend.

01:10:53.983 --> 01:10:55.952
And number two, I'm going to bed

01:10:56.252 --> 01:10:57.880
'cause you're a buzzkill.

01:11:03.493 --> 01:11:05.485
<i>Paul tells us that...</i>

01:11:05.595 --> 01:11:07.564
even if you can
speak the language

01:11:07.663 --> 01:11:12.465
of both man and
angels, if you lack love,

01:11:12.568 --> 01:11:13.695
brothers and sisters,

01:11:13.803 --> 01:11:16.432
you're just making
a lot of noise.

01:11:16.539 --> 01:11:19.998
<i>Maybe you're the
world's smartest person</i>

01:11:20.309 --> 01:11:24.303
<i>and you have a great faith
that can move mountains</i>

01:11:24.413 --> 01:11:26.678
or you give all your
money to the poor

01:11:26.783 --> 01:11:29.878
or you give your
body over to hardship.

01:11:29.986 --> 01:11:33.718
My Bible says, without love,

01:11:33.823 --> 01:11:36.383
you say nothing.

01:11:36.492 --> 01:11:40.293
<i>Without love, you gain nothing.</i>

01:11:40.396 --> 01:11:42.558
Without love,

01:11:42.665 --> 01:11:45.499
<i>you are nothing.</i>

01:12:02.518 --> 01:12:04.077
Hey, Adam.

01:12:04.387 --> 01:12:06.481
- Hey.
- Pastor Dave?

01:12:06.589 --> 01:12:07.852
Is it true?

01:12:07.957 --> 01:12:09.585
I don't... I don't know...

01:12:09.692 --> 01:12:10.955
- Is it? Tell me.
- Adam!

01:12:13.596 --> 01:12:15.690
- You killed Jude, didn't you?
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:12:15.798 --> 01:12:17.838
- Take it easy, pal.
- Get off of me! Get off of me!

01:12:19.435 --> 01:12:20.903
What is wrong with you?

01:12:23.973 --> 01:12:25.965
Hey, man, what's going on?

01:12:30.479 --> 01:12:32.471
That is messed up.

01:12:43.926 --> 01:12:45.360
Sign with that pen.

01:12:45.461 --> 01:12:46.656
What am I signing?

01:12:46.762 --> 01:12:48.073
Just saying I just
took your fingerprints

01:12:48.097 --> 01:12:49.395
and you're just being booked in.

01:12:49.498 --> 01:12:50.932
Is this, like, a mug shot?

01:12:51.033 --> 01:12:52.661
Yes.

01:12:52.768 --> 01:12:54.930
<i>After a shocking confrontation</i>

01:12:55.037 --> 01:12:58.132
<i>by Reverend David Hill on
Hadleigh campus, the suspect</i>

01:12:58.441 --> 01:13:00.501
has been identified
as 21-year-old

01:13:00.610 --> 01:13:02.943
Hadleigh student
Adam Richertson.

01:13:03.045 --> 01:13:05.378
The college senior
has no criminal record

01:13:05.481 --> 01:13:07.074
and no history of violence,

01:13:07.383 --> 01:13:09.079
which has left many
people wondering

01:13:09.385 --> 01:13:12.480
what inspired this
deadly attack on a church.

01:13:16.792 --> 01:13:18.784
I'm so sorry.

01:13:22.765 --> 01:13:24.996
<i>This is beyond messed up.</i>

01:13:25.101 --> 01:13:26.399
I know Adam.

01:13:26.502 --> 01:13:29.097
He's a good dude... sincerely.

01:13:29.405 --> 01:13:32.807
And Pastor Dave needs to
take a page from his own book.

01:13:32.909 --> 01:13:34.138
So, you know what?

01:13:34.443 --> 01:13:36.071
We're having a
protest Friday night.

01:13:36.178 --> 01:13:37.510
Saint James.

01:13:37.613 --> 01:13:39.514
Make sure your voice is heard.

01:13:39.615 --> 01:13:41.083
Be there. Be mad.

01:13:41.183 --> 01:13:44.984
'Cause this fight
is far from over.

01:13:47.456 --> 01:13:49.049
Have you seen this?

01:13:51.060 --> 01:13:52.756
Media works both ways.

01:13:52.862 --> 01:13:55.024
This gives us a real shot.

01:13:55.131 --> 01:13:56.759
Get the team working on it.

01:13:56.866 --> 01:14:00.200
I'm gonna send a gift
basket to Reverend Dave.

01:14:03.839 --> 01:14:05.671
<i>We condemn</i>

01:14:05.775 --> 01:14:09.439
the hateful actions
of Adam Richertson

01:14:09.545 --> 01:14:12.777
in the strongest possible terms.

01:14:12.882 --> 01:14:14.748
They do not represent the values

01:14:14.850 --> 01:14:17.115
of our esteemed
Hadleigh University.

01:14:17.219 --> 01:14:20.781
We will not stand for
violence or discrimination

01:14:20.890 --> 01:14:23.758
in any form, of any people,

01:14:23.859 --> 01:14:27.921
regardless of their religious
backgrounds and beliefs.

01:14:28.030 --> 01:14:31.057
We've taken the immediate
steps to expel Mr. Richertson,

01:14:31.167 --> 01:14:33.159
and we have encouraged the state

01:14:33.469 --> 01:14:37.565
to prosecute him to the
fullest extent of the law.

01:14:37.673 --> 01:14:40.142
None of this, however,

01:14:40.242 --> 01:14:44.043
should excuse the actions
of Reverend Dave Hill.

01:14:44.146 --> 01:14:48.584
His outburst has made
our position stronger:

01:14:48.684 --> 01:14:50.949
that Saint James
Church has become

01:14:51.053 --> 01:14:53.989
a beacon of violence
and controversy,

01:14:54.090 --> 01:14:57.720
and it has no place here

01:14:57.827 --> 01:15:00.092
on Hadleigh University campus.

01:15:00.196 --> 01:15:01.824
Good day.

01:15:07.903 --> 01:15:09.531
So, Reverend Hill
goes after Ellsworth.

01:15:09.638 --> 01:15:10.901
Now Ellsworth fires back.

01:15:11.007 --> 01:15:12.737
And meanwhile, this
kid Adam Richertson

01:15:12.842 --> 01:15:14.208
is caught in the crossfire.

01:15:14.510 --> 01:15:16.430
- Judge, this kid killed somebody.
- Oh, come on.

01:15:16.579 --> 01:15:18.590
- It was an accident. Everybody knows that.
- Can't forget it.

01:15:18.614 --> 01:15:19.658
Look, a judge and
jury's gonna decide that.

01:15:19.682 --> 01:15:20.762
Speaking of judge and jury,

01:15:20.816 --> 01:15:22.227
who's gonna hold this
reverend accountable?

01:15:22.251 --> 01:15:23.962
Okay, there's a big
difference between a death,

01:15:23.986 --> 01:15:25.682
okay, and-and a
fight, but this reverend

01:15:25.788 --> 01:15:27.620
did attack this
kid, and now he's

01:15:27.723 --> 01:15:29.715
calling for the kid to get
put away for 30 years?

01:15:29.825 --> 01:15:31.203
- That's insane.
- Well, and there you have it.

01:15:31.227 --> 01:15:33.219
Both sides are totally fired up.

01:15:33.529 --> 01:15:35.760
Huge protest is
planned for the weekend.

01:15:35.865 --> 01:15:37.561
And this is teed
up for disaster.

01:15:37.666 --> 01:15:39.658
That's the sign of
the times, isn't it?

01:15:39.769 --> 01:15:40.930
Everybody's yelling.

01:15:41.037 --> 01:15:42.596
- Nobody's listening.
- Absolutely.

01:15:43.839 --> 01:15:45.017
<i>It doesn't make sense.</i>

01:15:45.041 --> 01:15:46.566
<i>Nothing makes sense.</i>

01:15:47.810 --> 01:15:50.644
Adam never meant to hurt anyone.

01:15:50.746 --> 01:15:53.944
I'm not saying he shouldn't
own up to what he did, but...

01:15:54.050 --> 01:15:56.178
I just don't see
God's mercy here.

01:15:56.285 --> 01:15:58.015
Especially not from Pastor Dave.

01:15:58.120 --> 01:15:59.816
He's human, Keaton.

01:15:59.922 --> 01:16:01.891
Yeah, but he's supposed
to be a man of God.

01:16:01.991 --> 01:16:03.789
What kind of example is that?

01:16:03.893 --> 01:16:05.156
I mean, if being a Christian

01:16:05.261 --> 01:16:07.025
doesn't affect the
way we act, then...

01:16:08.631 --> 01:16:11.226
how do we actually
know that our values

01:16:11.333 --> 01:16:14.326
and beliefs are any more
valid than anyone else's?

01:16:18.040 --> 01:16:20.066
Can I show you something?

01:16:24.146 --> 01:16:27.207
A friend sent this to me
when I was in high school.

01:16:34.790 --> 01:16:36.691
It was inspiring.

01:16:36.792 --> 01:16:37.953
It's why I came to Hadleigh.

01:16:38.060 --> 01:16:39.824
I wanted to be a
part of something.

01:16:39.929 --> 01:16:41.898
At the time, I'd never even

01:16:41.997 --> 01:16:45.297
considered that
God could be dead.

01:16:48.337 --> 01:16:50.806
But now...

01:16:54.176 --> 01:16:55.667
It's okay, Keaton.

01:16:55.778 --> 01:16:58.714
It's good to ask
difficult questions.

01:16:58.814 --> 01:17:00.112
God can use it.

01:17:00.216 --> 01:17:02.845
He's not afraid of
your uncertainty.

01:17:02.952 --> 01:17:04.921
But I am.

01:17:06.355 --> 01:17:09.018
You know, I... I think
about John the Baptist.

01:17:09.125 --> 01:17:12.254
If anyone should've been
sure about Jesus, it was him.

01:17:12.361 --> 01:17:14.762
And John said, "I've
seen, and I testify

01:17:14.864 --> 01:17:17.231
that this is the Son of God."

01:17:17.333 --> 01:17:21.794
And then he got locked
up in Herod's little jail cell,

01:17:21.904 --> 01:17:23.348
and the doubts started
messing with his head.

01:17:23.372 --> 01:17:24.932
"What if I'm wrong
about this Jesus guy?

01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:26.800
"What if all the stories
I've heard about him

01:17:26.876 --> 01:17:28.811
healing people... what
if it's just ridiculous?"

01:17:28.911 --> 01:17:30.243
So John sent some of his friends

01:17:30.346 --> 01:17:33.282
to watch Jesus and report back.

01:17:33.382 --> 01:17:38.150
And Jesus told them, "Tell
John what you've seen and heard.

01:17:38.254 --> 01:17:40.951
"The blind receive their sight.

01:17:41.056 --> 01:17:42.422
"The lame walk.

01:17:42.725 --> 01:17:44.250
"The lepers are cleansed.

01:17:44.360 --> 01:17:46.261
The deaf hear."

01:17:46.362 --> 01:17:48.092
John needed to doubt.

01:17:48.197 --> 01:17:49.961
Why, though?

01:17:50.065 --> 01:17:54.264
Because... uncertainty
led to the pursuit of truth.

01:17:57.273 --> 01:18:00.038
I know it hurts...

01:18:00.142 --> 01:18:02.168
to be in the fire.

01:18:03.746 --> 01:18:05.874
And as painful and...

01:18:05.981 --> 01:18:08.678
confusing as all of this is,

01:18:08.784 --> 01:18:12.721
it just might be exactly where
God wants you right now.

01:18:16.926 --> 01:18:18.155
Well, it ain't good.

01:18:18.260 --> 01:18:19.580
Public opinion,
your reputation...

01:18:19.728 --> 01:18:21.162
It's all gonna take a hit.

01:18:21.263 --> 01:18:23.129
I guess we'll have
to wait and see.

01:18:23.232 --> 01:18:25.827
The kid confessed,
so... that helps.

01:18:25.935 --> 01:18:27.927
I just... I want to know
what you were thinking.

01:18:28.037 --> 01:18:29.869
I wasn't thinking, obviously.

01:18:29.972 --> 01:18:32.271
You get an anonymous text,
then you go nuts on somebody?

01:18:32.374 --> 01:18:35.469
I'm not interested in
rehashing this, okay?

01:18:38.013 --> 01:18:40.107
Sorry, folks.

01:18:50.426 --> 01:18:52.952
What's going on with you?

01:18:53.062 --> 01:18:55.031
I'm a mess. I don't
know what I'm doing,

01:18:55.130 --> 01:18:56.723
I don't know what
God wants me to do,

01:18:56.832 --> 01:18:58.743
and I don't know why any
of this is even happening.

01:18:58.767 --> 01:19:00.445
- First, you gotta settle down.
- Oh, I'm sure...

01:19:00.469 --> 01:19:02.480
I'm sure this is fun for you.
You get a front-row seat

01:19:02.504 --> 01:19:05.064
to watch your little brother,
Dave, just self-destruct.

01:19:05.174 --> 01:19:07.803
That's probably why you drove
down here in the first place.

01:19:12.915 --> 01:19:14.474
Where are you going?

01:19:14.783 --> 01:19:16.217
Oh, I'm walking.

01:19:16.318 --> 01:19:17.479
You can't.

01:19:17.786 --> 01:19:19.914
- Watch me.
- Pearce.

01:19:21.323 --> 01:19:22.757
What?

01:19:23.959 --> 01:19:26.190
You have the car keys.

01:20:05.334 --> 01:20:06.927
Dave.

01:20:07.036 --> 01:20:08.868
Hey, Roland.

01:20:10.339 --> 01:20:12.240
How you doing?

01:20:12.341 --> 01:20:13.969
Doing all right.

01:20:14.076 --> 01:20:18.980
You're sure on TV a lot
for someone doing all right.

01:20:19.081 --> 01:20:20.879
All this business
with Tom Ellsworth.

01:20:20.983 --> 01:20:22.884
And now the boy.

01:20:22.985 --> 01:20:24.510
Well, I didn't
ask for this fight.

01:20:24.820 --> 01:20:27.813
Mm, that's a
fact, but here it is.

01:20:27.923 --> 01:20:30.552
Keep your eye on
what's important.

01:20:30.859 --> 01:20:33.419
I think what's important
is that Christians stop

01:20:33.529 --> 01:20:35.589
rolling over all the time.

01:20:35.898 --> 01:20:37.833
When is it our right to fight?

01:20:37.933 --> 01:20:39.561
I'm tired of being
pushed around.

01:20:39.868 --> 01:20:41.336
I'm tired of turning
the other cheek.

01:20:41.437 --> 01:20:43.429
Oh, so now you're tired.

01:20:43.539 --> 01:20:46.168
A minute ago, you
were doing all right.

01:20:46.275 --> 01:20:47.937
I'm just saying,
I think it's time

01:20:48.043 --> 01:20:49.909
that Christians stand
up for themselves.

01:20:53.382 --> 01:20:55.476
Well...

01:20:55.584 --> 01:20:59.146
people were drawn to
Jesus because of His...

01:20:59.254 --> 01:21:01.155
His love.

01:21:01.256 --> 01:21:03.885
His patience and kindness.

01:21:03.992 --> 01:21:06.928
He managed to preach the truth

01:21:07.029 --> 01:21:09.863
without losing
Himself in the bargain.

01:21:09.965 --> 01:21:11.866
He was gentle with the meek

01:21:11.967 --> 01:21:15.199
and hard as a rock
with the arrogant.

01:21:15.304 --> 01:21:19.901
And when He talked to
the foolish, He was patient

01:21:20.008 --> 01:21:23.536
and never became a fool Himself.

01:21:23.645 --> 01:21:26.877
And He was never proud, David.

01:21:26.982 --> 01:21:30.885
This has nothing to
do with pride, Roland.

01:21:30.986 --> 01:21:34.388
And no offense, but maybe
you'd understand a little better

01:21:34.490 --> 01:21:36.459
if you were the
one being attacked.

01:21:36.558 --> 01:21:39.323
Brother, who do you
think you're talking to?

01:21:39.428 --> 01:21:41.329
I'm a black preacher
in the Deep South.

01:21:41.430 --> 01:21:43.456
I could build you a
church with all the bricks

01:21:43.565 --> 01:21:45.659
been thrown through my windows.

01:21:47.369 --> 01:21:50.066
You're right. I'm sorry.

01:21:52.241 --> 01:21:54.608
You gotta work through the pain.

01:21:57.312 --> 01:22:01.147
We cannot respond
to hate with more hate.

01:22:01.250 --> 01:22:04.652
And don't forget.

01:22:06.021 --> 01:22:09.185
We are called to be a light

01:22:09.291 --> 01:22:11.658
in the darkness.

01:22:21.303 --> 01:22:23.033
I miss Jude.

01:22:29.445 --> 01:22:31.710
And I miss You, too, Lord.

01:22:34.983 --> 01:22:37.612
I'm trying to do the
right thing. I just...

01:22:40.656 --> 01:22:43.421
I don't know what
that is anymore.

01:22:48.697 --> 01:22:50.427
Hey there.

01:22:50.532 --> 01:22:52.660
Just checking on you.

01:22:54.102 --> 01:22:55.365
I saw the news.

01:22:55.471 --> 01:22:58.566
I can't imagine
what you're feeling.

01:22:58.674 --> 01:23:00.973
<i>I'd like to see you.</i>

01:23:01.076 --> 01:23:03.545
<i>How about a little adventure?</i>

01:23:03.645 --> 01:23:06.308
<i>Um, I'm gonna
send you a drop pin.</i>

01:23:06.415 --> 01:23:08.680
<i>I'll meet you there in an hour?</i>

01:23:11.153 --> 01:23:13.315
It's my church away from church.

01:23:13.422 --> 01:23:16.051
It's where I come
to be alone with God.

01:23:18.093 --> 01:23:20.528
- I can see why.
- Mm-hmm.

01:23:22.764 --> 01:23:24.733
What do you got there?

01:23:26.368 --> 01:23:28.735
I light a candle for
people I'm praying for.

01:23:30.005 --> 01:23:31.496
Uh...

01:23:31.607 --> 01:23:33.439
folks I meet at the restaurant,

01:23:33.542 --> 01:23:35.602
friends from A.A.

01:23:36.678 --> 01:23:37.771
You.

01:23:42.117 --> 01:23:46.145
I just love the way He uses
other people in our lives to...

01:23:46.255 --> 01:23:48.087
to bring us comfort.

01:23:48.190 --> 01:23:52.525
To remind us that we're loved.

01:23:55.197 --> 01:23:57.757
I think you need to
be reminded right now.

01:24:00.569 --> 01:24:03.038
God is here.

01:24:04.139 --> 01:24:05.573
I'm here.

01:24:07.409 --> 01:24:09.275
And you're loved.

01:24:27.195 --> 01:24:29.630
I thought you were out with Meg.

01:24:29.731 --> 01:24:31.632
You screw that up, too?

01:24:31.733 --> 01:24:33.565
What are you doing?

01:24:33.669 --> 01:24:36.161
Listen, I'm gonna fly
back to Chicago tonight.

01:24:36.271 --> 01:24:38.103
I left you the name
and, uh, number

01:24:38.206 --> 01:24:39.606
of an attorney friend of mine.

01:24:39.708 --> 01:24:42.337
She'll take good
care of you. My treat.

01:24:42.444 --> 01:24:44.538
Why? Just because
we had an argument?

01:24:44.646 --> 01:24:47.206
- It's just time.
- Pearce, are you kidding me?

01:24:49.818 --> 01:24:51.377
You know what?

01:24:51.486 --> 01:24:53.114
Go ahead.

01:24:53.221 --> 01:24:55.747
Oh, I haven't done
enough for you, huh?

01:24:55.857 --> 01:24:57.621
Come down here,
put my life on hold,

01:24:57.726 --> 01:24:59.558
but I'm the bad guy
now 'cause I'm bailing?

01:24:59.661 --> 01:25:01.254
Is that it?

01:25:01.363 --> 01:25:03.161
Let's not get into
it. It's not worth it.

01:25:03.265 --> 01:25:05.257
No, I-I think it's worth
it. Let's get into it.

01:25:05.367 --> 01:25:07.359
It's water under the bridge.

01:25:07.469 --> 01:25:09.233
I forgave you years ago.

01:25:09.338 --> 01:25:10.601
You forgave me?

01:25:10.706 --> 01:25:12.698
For what exactly? For leaving?

01:25:12.808 --> 01:25:14.140
You forced me out.

01:25:14.242 --> 01:25:15.437
You and Mom and Dad. All you.

01:25:15.544 --> 01:25:17.274
Give me a break. No
one forced you out.

01:25:17.379 --> 01:25:18.472
Oh, yes, you did.

01:25:18.580 --> 01:25:19.780
I wasn't welcome in this house

01:25:19.881 --> 01:25:21.361
once I started asking
tough questions.

01:25:21.450 --> 01:25:23.442
Is that what they
were? Tough questions?

01:25:23.552 --> 01:25:25.487
Oh, "Why does
God allow bad things

01:25:25.587 --> 01:25:26.816
to happen to good people?"

01:25:27.122 --> 01:25:28.562
Or, "How do we even
know God exists?"

01:25:28.657 --> 01:25:30.101
- Really?
- You should back off, little brother.

01:25:30.125 --> 01:25:31.593
Maybe you were
just trying to impress

01:25:31.693 --> 01:25:34.162
a coed with how worldly
and forward-thinking you were.

01:25:34.262 --> 01:25:35.560
I guess your Christian roots

01:25:35.664 --> 01:25:37.141
- were too provincial.
- Well, at least

01:25:37.165 --> 01:25:39.293
I know what's happening
in the world five miles

01:25:39.401 --> 01:25:41.802
- outside the county line.
- You're right, I don't know.

01:25:41.903 --> 01:25:44.270
And I don't know why
you left me to take care

01:25:44.373 --> 01:25:46.308
of Mom and Dad
when they were sick.

01:25:46.408 --> 01:25:47.685
Why did you leave
me to take care

01:25:47.709 --> 01:25:49.803
of everything after
they were gone?

01:25:49.911 --> 01:25:52.676
Do you have any idea what
you did to Mom and Dad?

01:25:52.781 --> 01:25:54.147
You broke their hearts.

01:25:54.249 --> 01:25:56.480
You're the one
that broke my heart!

01:25:56.585 --> 01:25:58.611
You really don't
get that, do you?

01:25:58.720 --> 01:26:00.348
You didn't take the time

01:26:00.455 --> 01:26:02.390
to understand what
I was going through.

01:26:02.491 --> 01:26:05.552
I was trying to sort
out my own faith.

01:26:05.661 --> 01:26:08.392
My own sense of God.

01:26:08.497 --> 01:26:10.796
I was changing, and
you all hated me for it,

01:26:10.899 --> 01:26:13.494
and that's the truth, David.

01:27:54.269 --> 01:27:56.568
What am I doing wrong?

01:27:59.875 --> 01:28:01.776
Just show me.

01:28:06.448 --> 01:28:07.882
Please.

01:29:01.870 --> 01:29:03.930
<i>As the battle rages
on in Hope Springs,</i>

01:29:04.039 --> 01:29:06.941
<i>police say they're expecting
hundreds of students and locals</i>

01:29:07.042 --> 01:29:09.807
<i>for a protest outside Saint
James Church tonight...</i>

01:29:09.911 --> 01:29:12.745
<i>Some showing support for
the church, others continuing</i>

01:29:12.848 --> 01:29:14.783
<i>to call for its removal.</i>

01:29:19.654 --> 01:29:21.555
Keaton.

01:29:21.656 --> 01:29:25.718
Did you ever even stop to
ask why Adam threw that brick?

01:29:25.827 --> 01:29:28.126
He's tired of feeling
judged and rejected

01:29:28.430 --> 01:29:31.764
by the people who should
be loving and accepting.

01:29:31.867 --> 01:29:33.110
You want to know
why our generation's

01:29:33.134 --> 01:29:34.568
leaving the church?

01:29:34.669 --> 01:29:36.001
It's because the
whole world knows

01:29:36.104 --> 01:29:37.824
what the church is
against, but it's getting

01:29:37.873 --> 01:29:39.739
harder and harder
to know what it's for.

01:29:42.010 --> 01:29:43.979
You're right.

01:29:45.981 --> 01:29:48.075
There's something I need to do.

01:29:48.383 --> 01:29:50.545
Will you come with me?

01:29:53.054 --> 01:29:55.114
KEATON; <i>Pastor
Dave is here to see you.</i>

01:29:55.423 --> 01:29:56.891
<i>If you want.</i>

01:29:58.994 --> 01:30:00.587
Sure.

01:30:00.695 --> 01:30:02.425
Okay.

01:30:25.053 --> 01:30:27.045
I'm the one that sent
you that message.

01:30:29.891 --> 01:30:31.860
I needed you to know.

01:30:36.865 --> 01:30:39.926
I guess I was
hoping that you'd...

01:30:40.035 --> 01:30:41.867
Forgive.

01:30:50.211 --> 01:30:52.908
This is, uh... this
is Jude's Bible.

01:30:59.487 --> 01:31:01.456
He'd want you to have it.

01:31:10.999 --> 01:31:13.525
I'm so sorry.

01:31:15.770 --> 01:31:17.762
About Jude, I am so...

01:31:17.872 --> 01:31:20.000
sorry.

01:31:37.025 --> 01:31:40.860
We want to plead
for leniency for Adam.

01:31:40.962 --> 01:31:42.828
I'm the only witness
the state has.

01:31:42.931 --> 01:31:44.797
I'll tell the D.A. what I saw...

01:31:44.899 --> 01:31:47.528
That Jude's death couldn't
have been premeditated.

01:31:47.635 --> 01:31:49.729
I spoke with Jude's parents.

01:31:49.838 --> 01:31:51.932
They feel the same.

01:31:52.040 --> 01:31:53.872
We're hoping the state

01:31:53.975 --> 01:31:55.807
will agree to a lesser charge.

01:31:55.910 --> 01:31:58.277
Drop it from a felony
to a misdemeanor.

01:31:58.580 --> 01:32:00.776
Hopefully he doesn't have
to do any more jail time.

01:32:00.882 --> 01:32:02.680
Why?

01:32:02.784 --> 01:32:05.618
The boy shouldn't be collateral
damage for our fight, Tom.

01:32:09.724 --> 01:32:12.785
There's gonna be a big
protest tonight at the church.

01:32:12.894 --> 01:32:15.762
Town's on edge. The
whole thing has gone too far.

01:32:15.864 --> 01:32:18.299
- Didn't have to.
- You're right.

01:32:18.600 --> 01:32:20.193
And I'm sorry.

01:32:21.770 --> 01:32:24.137
I truly am.

01:32:25.940 --> 01:32:27.602
For everything.

01:32:37.052 --> 01:32:38.748
Me, too.

01:32:38.853 --> 01:32:40.151
My part.

01:32:48.830 --> 01:32:50.958
So, what about the church?

01:32:57.839 --> 01:32:58.932
The church must go!

01:32:59.040 --> 01:33:00.338
Enough is enough!

01:33:00.642 --> 01:33:01.701
The church must go!

01:33:19.828 --> 01:33:22.024
Can I talk to them?
This is my church.

01:33:33.908 --> 01:33:36.707
One God! One truth! One God!

01:33:36.811 --> 01:33:38.006
One truth!

01:33:43.351 --> 01:33:44.979
The church must go!
Enough is enough!

01:33:45.086 --> 01:33:46.611
The church must go!

01:33:46.721 --> 01:33:49.748
Enough is enough!
The church must go!

01:33:49.858 --> 01:33:51.690
Can I have your attention?

01:33:51.793 --> 01:33:53.237
The church must go!

01:33:53.261 --> 01:33:56.163
Can I please say something?

01:33:56.264 --> 01:33:58.130
Get out of here!

01:33:58.233 --> 01:34:00.964
Excuse me. May
I... may I just say...

01:34:01.069 --> 01:34:02.697
may I say something?

01:34:06.808 --> 01:34:09.209
May I please say something?

01:34:10.345 --> 01:34:12.905
Please. Please.

01:34:13.014 --> 01:34:15.074
Let's hear what
the man has to say.

01:34:16.851 --> 01:34:18.183
Thank you.

01:34:20.989 --> 01:34:23.083
I came here tonight

01:34:23.191 --> 01:34:27.253
to ask all of you
for your forgiveness.

01:34:30.932 --> 01:34:34.096
The other night, I stood
before this burnt altar,

01:34:34.202 --> 01:34:38.936
and I heard God's voice for
the first time in a long time.

01:34:40.808 --> 01:34:42.743
Couldn't have been clearer.

01:34:44.746 --> 01:34:47.682
He said, "This building...

01:34:47.782 --> 01:34:50.047
is not My church."

01:34:50.151 --> 01:34:54.714
Although Saint James
has meant everything to me,

01:34:54.822 --> 01:34:56.688
although it's been
my whole life...

